module.exports={"secrets-bahia-mita-surf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Both are adults-only Mexican all-inclusives in the Secrets portfolio at the same price tier, with near-identical scores for cleanliness (9.3 each), service (9.2 each), sleep quality (9.0 vs 9.1), and overall (8.9 vs 8.8). The sharpest divergence is the beach rating: Bahia Mita scores a 5.0 versus Playa Mujeres' 7.5, a significant gap that reflects the Pacific surf conditions at Punta de Mita versus the calm Caribbean waters near Cancún. Playa Mujeres also rates higher on atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.7), food (8.0 vs 7.8), and pool (8.0 vs 7.8). Bahia Mita counters with a superior room score (9.1 vs 9.0), a pets-allowed policy unique to that property, and a Pacific surf-and-spa identity that attracts guests drawn to Riviera Nayarit's rugged coastline. Playa Mujeres adds a full golf course and tennis courts, making it the stronger choice for sports-minded couples. Location scores are comparable, though each serves a fundamentally different Mexican coast.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or solo travelers who want a Pacific Mexico experience in the Riviera Nayarit near Punta de Mita, prioritize exceptional rooms and cleanliness over beach swimming, are comfortable with surf conditions, or want to bring a pet to a high-end all-inclusive.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults-only couples who want a calmer Caribbean beach, a higher food and atmosphere rating, and on-site golf and tennis alongside the full Secrets amenity package near Cancún. Golfers, tennis players, and beach loungers will find this the more well-rounded option.","whenToVisit":"Bahia Mita on Mexico's Pacific coast is best November through April when dry-season conditions prevail; summer months bring humidity and Pacific swell. Playa Mujeres on the Caribbean side also peaks December through April, avoiding hurricane season (June–November). Both properties offer the best combination of weather, calm seas, and value in the winter high season.","activities":"Bahia Mita guests can surf or watch world-class breaks nearby, explore the Marieta Islands by boat, visit the charming town of Sayulita, or take whale-watching excursions in season. Playa Mujeres guests can play on-site golf and tennis, snorkel the Caribbean reefs, visit Isla Mujeres by ferry, or make the short trip into Cancún for nightlife, cenote tours, and Mayan ruins."},"dreams-huatulco-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Huatulco and Secrets Playa Mujeres both sit at the $$$$ price tier with near-identical overall ratings (8.9 vs 8.8), but diverge sharply in audience and amenity profile. Dreams is a family all-inclusive on Oaxaca's Pacific coast with a kids club for under-4s, babysitting, archery, snorkelling, windsurfing, and fishing — a strong activity roster for mixed-age groups. Secrets Playa Mujeres is adults-only near Cancún, with a golf course, heated pools, swim-up bar, nightclub, and tennis, built for couples seeking quiet and polish. The ratings tell the real story: Secrets scores notably higher on food (8.0 vs 7.5), pool (8.0 vs 6.9), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.4), room (9.0 vs 8.6), service (9.2 vs 9.0), sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.7), and cleanliness (9.3 vs 9.1). Dreams counters with a more remote, culturally distinct Pacific setting versus Secrets' proximity to Cancún's Caribbean infrastructure. Both offer equal value scores (8.6), but Secrets delivers a measurably more refined product for non-families.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who want a Pacific Mexico all-inclusive in the quieter, less commercialized Huatulco bay system, with a full kids club including under-4s, babysitting, watersports like snorkelling and windsurfing, and strong service scores in a genuinely off-the-beaten-path setting.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want a polished, adults-only Caribbean Mexico all-inclusive near Cancún with golf, a heated pool, swim-up bar, nightclub, and some of the highest room and service scores in the category — without the noise and activity of a family resort.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts enjoy Mexico's dry season from November through April. Huatulco on the Pacific coast sees its wettest months June through September but remains accessible year-round. Playa Mujeres near Cancún falls in the Atlantic hurricane belt, making June through November riskier, with September the most active month. For either resort, December through March offers the most reliable weather and peak atmosphere.","activities":"At Dreams Huatulco, guests can snorkel the protected Tangolunda bay, windsurf, fish, try archery onsite, or take day trips to the Oaxacan coffee highlands and Hierve el Agua petrified waterfalls nearby. At Secrets Playa Mujeres, guests can play the onsite golf course, take a ferry to Isla Mujeres for snorkelling and town exploration, or access Cancún's broader dining and nightlife scene just to the south."},"secrets-playa-esmeralda-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Esmeralda sits on a remote stretch of Dominican Republic coastline in Miches, a less-developed area that earns it a beach rating of 8.5 versus Playa Mujeres' 7.5, but its location score of 7.8 reflects the trade-off of getting there. Secrets Playa Mujeres is just north of Cancun in Punta Sam, earning a location score of 8.9, and comes loaded with amenities Esmeralda lacks entirely: a golf course, swim-up bar, tennis, evening entertainment, and a nightclub. Playa Mujeres scores higher overall (8.8 vs 8.2), with notably stronger cleanliness (9.3 vs 8.8), service (9.2 vs 8.6), room quality (9.0 vs 8.3), and value (8.6 vs 7.9) despite carrying a higher price tag. Esmeralda counters with a superior beach experience and a quieter, more secluded atmosphere. Both share the same food rating of 8.0 and identical sleep quality at 9.1. Esmeralda suits those prioritizing natural seclusion; Playa Mujeres suits those wanting polished amenities and stronger overall execution.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a secluded, nature-forward Dominican Republic escape on one of the Caribbean's quieter coastlines, and who prioritize beach quality and tranquility over extensive amenities. Ideal for couples seeking genuine remoteness and strong sleep quality without needing a nightclub or golf course.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults who want a high-performing, amenity-rich Mexican resort near Cancun with golf, tennis, a swim-up bar, nightclub, and consistently excellent service and cleanliness scores. Best for couples or solo travelers who want polished execution and easy access to broader Yucatan attractions.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Playa Esmeralda is best visited November through April when the Dominican Republic's north coast sees lower rainfall and calmer seas. Secrets Playa Mujeres in the Mexican Caribbean is ideal from December through April, avoiding peak hurricane season. Both resorts sit in the Atlantic hurricane belt, so summer and early fall carry weather risk worth factoring into travel insurance decisions.","activities":"At Secrets Playa Esmeralda, guests can explore the undeveloped Miches coastline, use the spa and gym, and take excursions into the nearby Los Haitises National Park ecosystem. At Secrets Playa Mujeres, guests can play golf on the on-site course, use the tennis courts, enjoy the swim-up bar, and access nearby Cancun, Isla Mujeres ferry crossings, and cenote day trips from one of Mexico's most connected resort corridors."},"breathless-punta-cana-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Punta Cana and Secrets Playa Mujeres share the same overall rating of 8.8 and both sit at the $$$$  adults-only tier, but Secrets pulls ahead on nearly every experiential metric: food (8.0 vs 7.6), beach (7.5 vs 6.5), pool (8.0 vs 7.4), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.4), room (9.0 vs 8.6), service (9.2 vs 8.9), cleanliness (9.3 vs 9.0), and sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.3). Breathless counters with a casino, lazy river, snorkelling, and diving — amenities Secrets lacks — plus a livelier, more nightclub-forward energy that suits guests who want active programming over refinement. Secrets sits on a quieter peninsula north of Cancún with a golf course, heated pool, free Wi-Fi, and no-reservation dining, signalling a more polished, relaxed experience. If you want a buzzy Dominican adults-only all-inclusive with a casino, lazy river, diving, and nightclub energy, go to Breathless Punta Cana. If you want a quieter, more refined Mexican adults-only resort with superior rooms, service, and a golf course, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a high-energy Dominican all-inclusive with a casino, lazy river, diving, snorkelling, and a nightclub-driven atmosphere. Best for those who prioritise an active, party-friendly beach holiday over polished service or room quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults and couples who want a refined, quieter Mexican all-inclusive with standout rooms, exceptional service, a golf course, and no-reservation dining. Ideal for those willing to trade nightlife intensity for a more relaxed, upscale experience near Cancún.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when rainfall is low and temperatures are ideal. Punta Cana sits in the Atlantic hurricane corridor, making late August through October higher-risk; Secrets Playa Mujeres on Mexico's Caribbean coast faces similar storm exposure during the same window. Shoulder months of May and November offer better pricing at both with manageable weather risk.","activities":"Breathless guests can dive, snorkel, and kayak directly from the resort, or explore Punta Cana's dune buggies, zip lines, and cenote excursions nearby. Secrets Playa Mujeres guests have an on-site golf course, with Isla Mujeres ferry trips, Cancún's hotel zone, and Mesoamerican Reef snorkelling all within easy reach. Both resorts offer spa services, tennis, and evening entertainment on-site."},"dreams-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Playa Mujeres and Secrets Playa Mujeres are sister resorts sharing the same upscale Playa Mujeres corridor and identical price tier, so the choice comes down almost entirely to who you're traveling with. Dreams is a full family resort with a kids club, teen club, waterparks for all ages, lazy river, mini golf, babysitting, and rooms that accommodate five or more guests. Secrets is adults-only, stripping out all of that in favor of a quieter, more refined atmosphere. The ratings tell the story: Secrets edges Dreams on atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.6), service (9.2 vs 9.0), sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.9), value (8.6 vs 8.4), and cleanliness (9.3 vs 9.2). Dreams counters with a marginally higher overall score (8.9 vs 8.8) and broader amenity coverage. Food scores are nearly identical (7.9 vs 8.0). Both share the same beach rating (7.5) and pool score (8.0), suggesting the physical setting is essentially the same product split across two guest profiles.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of any age who want a high-end Mexican all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, a kids club from infancy through teens, babysitting, and large-group rooms, without sacrificing strong service and cleanliness scores.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want the same upscale Playa Mujeres setting without children present, and will appreciate the marginally better service scores, quieter sleep environment, heated pool, and tennis court in a more serene atmosphere.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in the Playa Mujeres area north of Cancun, making timing identical. December through April offers the driest, calmest weather and peak-season pricing. May and June are good value shoulder months before hurricane season intensifies July through October. November can offer solid deals as storm risk drops.","activities":"Both resorts share access to the same 27-hole Playa Mujeres golf course, spa facilities, swim-up bars, evening entertainment, and a nightclub on property. The broader area offers sport fishing, kitesurfing, snorkeling at Isla Mujeres a short ferry ride away, cenote diving, and day trips to Chichen Itza and the Tulum archaeological zone."},"dreams-dominicus-la-romana-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Dominicus La Romana is a large Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Bayahibe with a waterpark for little kids, teen club, kids club for under-4s, diving, snorkelling, watersports rentals, babysitting, and rooms for 5+ guests. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only Mexican resort in Punta Sam with a golf course, heated pool, tennis, and a markedly higher cleanliness rating of 9.3 versus 8.9, stronger room score of 9.0 versus 8.6, and better service at 9.2 versus 8.8. Dreams leads on location practicality for families at 8.8 but trails on food at 7.2 compared to Secrets' 8.0, and its pool rating of 6.9 falls well short of Secrets' 8.0. Secrets offers a quieter, more refined experience near Cancun with a golf course and noticeably superior rooms and service scores. If you want a full-featured Dominican Republic family all-inclusive with watersports, a kids waterpark, teen programming, and diving in Bayahibe, go to Dreams Dominicus. If you want a polished adults-only Mexican resort with golf, heated pool, tennis, and top-tier cleanliness and service scores, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a well-rounded Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a kids waterpark, dedicated clubs for toddlers through teens, diving, snorkelling, watersports rentals, and babysitting in a clean, highly rated Bayahibe setting.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples and groups who want a refined, adults-only Mexican resort near Cancun with a golf course, heated pool, tennis, and standout scores in cleanliness, room quality, and service in a tranquil Punta Sam setting.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when rainfall is minimal and conditions are reliably sunny. The Dominican Republic's Bayahibe area can see hurricane-season rain July through October, while Punta Sam near Cancun shares a similar Atlantic hurricane window. Shoulder months of May and November offer lower rates at both with generally acceptable weather and fewer crowds.","activities":"At Dreams Dominicus, guests can dive and snorkel the nearby Catalina Island reef, rent watersports equipment, and explore Altos de Chavon, a replica Mediterranean village a short drive away. At Secrets Playa Mujeres, guests can golf on the on-site course, play tennis, take a short trip to Isla Mujeres by ferry, or arrange excursions to Cancun's lagoon and cenotes."},"dreams-vista-cancun-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Vista Cancun Golf & Spa Resort is a large family all-inclusive in Cancun with a flowrider, waterpark for little kids, arcade, kids club for under-4s, teen club, babysitting, diving, windsurfing, and rooms for 5+ guests — a genuinely comprehensive family operation. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only all-inclusive in the quieter Punta Sam area near Playa Mujeres, with a swim-up bar, tennis, and notably stronger ratings across beach (7.5 vs 4.0), food (8.0 vs 7.6), pool (8.0 vs 7.4), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.1), sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.8), and service (9.2 vs 9.0). Both share the same overall rating (8.9 vs 8.8) and room score (9.0), but Dreams Vista wins on value (8.7 vs 8.6) and location (8.3 vs 8.9 to Secrets). The core split is simple: Dreams Vista is a feature-packed family resort with an average beach, while Secrets Playa Mujeres is a refined, quieter adults-only retreat with a meaningfully better beach and atmosphere.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want maximum activity coverage — flowrider, waterpark, arcade, kids club from infancy, teen club, diving, and watersports — in one large Cancun all-inclusive. The strong room and value scores make it especially attractive for families booking larger accommodations.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult groups who want a quieter, more polished all-inclusive experience near Playa Mujeres, where a better beach, stronger food ratings, swim-up bar, and higher sleep quality scores justify leaving Cancun's main hotel zone behind entirely.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from the Yucatan Peninsula's dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is low and temperatures hover in the mid-to-upper 20s Celsius. July and August are busy with families at Dreams Vista. Secrets Playa Mujeres offers a more peaceful experience year-round given its adults-only policy, though hurricane season (June–November) carries risk for both properties.","activities":"Dreams Vista guests can use the on-site flowrider, waterpark, arcade, and diving program, plus golf. Secrets Playa Mujeres guests have tennis, golf, and a swim-up bar, and the Playa Mujeres area offers world-class sport fishing, kitesurfing, and easy ferry access to Isla Mujeres. Both resorts offer evening entertainment, spa facilities, and snorkelling off the Yucatan coast."},"dreams-jade-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Jade and Secrets Playa Mujeres share the same overall rating (8.8) and price tier, but their guest profiles and on-the-ground experience diverge sharply. Dreams Jade is a family resort in Puerto Morelos with a kids club, teen club, babysitting, lazy river, archery, diving, fishing, and rooms for five or more — built around keeping families busy. Secrets Playa Mujeres is adults-only near Punta Sam, oriented around quiet refinement: its room score (9.0 vs 8.6), cleanliness (9.3 vs 8.9), service (9.2 vs 8.8), sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.6), and beach rating (7.5 vs 4.8) all run noticeably higher. Secrets also adds a golf course, a differentiator Dreams Jade lacks entirely. Dreams Jade's food rating (7.4) trails Secrets meaningfully (8.0). The tradeoff is breadth of family amenities versus a more polished, quieter adults experience. If you want a well-rounded Mexican family all-inclusive with a lazy river, kids programming, and activity variety, Dreams Jade delivers. If you want a cleaner, quieter adults-only resort with better food, rooms, and a golf course, Secrets Playa Mujeres wins.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages, including toddlers, who want a sprawling Mexican all-inclusive with a lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, diving, archery, and large rooms that sleep five or more — all without worrying about reservations for dinner.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or solo travelers who prioritize polished service, superior room quality, a genuinely good beach, and on-site golf in a quieter, adults-only Mexican resort setting where higher cleanliness and sleep quality scores reflect a more refined atmosphere.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's Yucatan dry season, roughly December through April, when humidity drops and rainfall is minimal. July and August bring heat and higher humidity but remain popular for families at Dreams Jade during school holidays. Hurricane season peaks September through October — rates drop but weather risk rises at both properties.","activities":"Dreams Jade guests can dive, fish, cycle, play tennis, and use the lazy river on-site, with Puerto Morelos's famous coral reef just offshore for snorkeling. Secrets Playa Mujeres centers on golf, tennis, spa, and evening entertainment, with Isla Mujeres reachable by ferry for day trips, and Cancun's broader restaurant and nightlife scene accessible from both resorts."},"dreams-estrella-del-mar-mazatlan-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Estrella del Mar Mazatlán is a family all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast with an overall rating of 9.0, exceptional room scores (9.5) and value (8.9), and an extensive lineup of family amenities including a kids club, lazy river, waterparks for both age groups, babysitting, and yoga. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only all-inclusive near Cancún on the Caribbean side, rated 8.8 overall, with stronger food (8.0 vs 7.6), beach (7.5 vs 6.8), and pool scores (8.0 vs 7.3), plus a nightclub and tennis courts. Dreams edges Secrets on room quality, value, and cleanliness, while Secrets wins on beach, pool, food, and atmosphere. The core split is family-versus-adults: Dreams is purpose-built for multigenerational trips with waterpark infrastructure and babysitting, while Secrets is a refined couples retreat near Cancún's Caribbean waters with a livelier nightlife offering. Dreams also sits in Mazatlán, a less-visited Pacific destination, whereas Secrets benefits from Cancún-area airlift and the Caribbean setting many guests specifically seek.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a Pacific Mexico all-inclusive with outstanding rooms, strong value, a lazy river, waterparks, babysitting, and a kids club, and who don't mind a beach and food program that lags slightly behind the rest of the resort's impressive scores.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want a polished Caribbean all-inclusive near Cancún with better food, beach, and pool ratings, a nightclub, tennis, and a quieter, romance-oriented atmosphere without children on property.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's dry season, roughly December through April, when humidity and rain are lowest. Mazatlán's Pacific side avoids the Gulf's hurricane exposure, making Dreams a safer bet in late summer and fall. Secrets Playa Mujeres sits in the Caribbean hurricane belt, so July through October carries more weather risk. Cancún's peak winter season brings crowds and higher prices; Mazatlán sees fewer international visitors year-round, offering a quieter experience even in high season.","activities":"Dreams guests can golf the on-site course, use the waterparks, join yoga classes, and explore Mazatlán's historic centro, malecón boardwalk, and sport-fishing scene nearby. Secrets guests have on-site golf, tennis, a spa, and access to the Punta Sam area's calm Caribbean waters, with Isla Mujeres—reachable by ferry—offering snorkelling, cycling, and a charming town just minutes from the resort."},"dreams-macao-beach-punta-cana-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Macao Beach Punta Cana is a large family all-inclusive on one of Punta Cana's most scenic beaches in the Dominican Republic, with a waterpark, lazy river, kids club for under-4s, teen club, archery, diving, snorkelling, babysitting, and rooms sleeping five or more. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only Mexican all-inclusive north of Cancún in the quieter Punta Sam area, with a golf course, heated pool, and spa anchoring a more serene, polished experience. Dreams edges ahead overall at 9.0 versus 8.8, and scores notably higher on food (7.6 vs 8.0 favors Secrets), while Secrets leads on service (9.2 vs 9.0), sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.9), and cleanliness (9.3 vs 9.2). Dreams wins on beach (7.8 vs 7.5) and pool atmosphere. The core divide is family infrastructure versus adults-only refinement: Dreams is built for multigenerational groups and active families, while Secrets offers a golf, spa, and tranquility-focused retreat with no children present.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, diving, and large rooms that sleep five or more, all on a naturally beautiful beach away from the busiest resort strips.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want a peaceful, upscale Mexican all-inclusive with a golf course, heated pool, full spa, and superior service and sleep quality in a quieter location north of Cancún, without the energy and noise of a family resort.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations share a similar Caribbean climate. December through April offers the driest, most reliable weather for both the Dominican Republic and Mexico's Yucatán coast. Dreams Macao benefits from Macao Beach's natural setting, which can see stronger surf outside peak season. Secrets Playa Mujeres sits in a calmer bay, making it slightly more weather-resilient. Both resorts carry hurricane-season risk from August through October.","activities":"Dreams Macao guests can dive, snorkel, kayak, use watersports rentals, play tennis and archery, use the waterpark, or explore nearby Macao Beach and Uvero Alto. Secrets Playa Mujeres guests can golf on an on-site course, use the spa, play tennis, snorkel the calm bay, or take day trips to Isla Mujeres, the Cancún hotel zone, and nearby cenotes, which are all within easy reach of Punta Sam."},"dreams-karibana-cartagena-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Karibana Cartagena and Secrets Playa Mujeres share the same overall rating (8.9 vs 8.8) and price tier, but diverge sharply in who they serve and how they perform on key metrics. Dreams Karibana is a family all-inclusive on Colombia's Caribbean coast with a kids club, babysitting, pets policy, and an on-site golf course, but its food (7.0), pool (6.9), beach (4.5), and atmosphere (6.8) ratings are notably weak. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only retreat north of Cancún in Mexico's Punta Sam area, with a heated pool, swim-up bar, nightclub, and tennis, and it outscores Dreams on food (8.0 vs 7.0), beach (7.5 vs 4.5), pool (8.0 vs 6.9), atmosphere (8.0 vs 6.8), service (9.2 vs 8.9), and cleanliness (9.3 vs 9.1). Dreams wins on location accessibility within Cartagena (8.2) and is the only option for families. If you want a family-friendly Colombian all-inclusive with a kids club and babysitting despite weaker beach and food scores, choose Dreams Karibana. If you want a polished adults-only Mexican resort with a strong beach, heated pool, swim-up bar, and superior service and dining, choose Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children, including infants, who want a well-appointed Colombian all-inclusive in Cartagena with a kids club, babysitting, pet-friendly policy, and excellent room quality and cleanliness, and who can accept a weaker beach and food program at the same premium price point.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who want a refined, adults-only Mexican all-inclusive near Cancún with a heated pool, swim-up bar, nightclub, tennis, and some of the strongest food, service, and beach ratings in its class, all without the noise and activity of a family resort.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Karibana in Cartagena is best visited December through April, Colombia's dry season, when heat and humidity are manageable and rainfall is minimal. Secrets Playa Mujeres near Cancún is also at its best December through April, avoiding the June–October hurricane season. Both resorts sit in peak demand over Christmas and New Year, so book well in advance for either destination during the northern winter holiday window.","activities":"At Dreams Karibana, guests can play golf on the on-site course, use the spa and gym, and explore the UNESCO-listed walled city of Cartagena nearby. At Secrets Playa Mujeres, on-site options include golf, tennis, a swim-up bar, nightclub, and spa, with Isla Mujeres ferry trips, Cancún shopping, and Mesoamerican reef snorkeling and diving easily accessible from the Punta Sam area."},"dreams-vallarta-bay-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Vallarta Bay is a family-oriented all-inclusive in Puerto Vallarta with a kids club, teen club, pool slide, babysitting, diving, fishing, and no-reservation dining, rated well for service (9.0) and cleanliness (9.0) but scoring notably lower on beach (6.0) and pool (6.9). Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only resort near Cancún in Punta Sam with a golf course, higher-rated food (8.0 vs 7.5), and meaningfully better scores across beach (7.5), pool (8.0), atmosphere (8.0), sleep quality (9.1), service (9.2), and cleanliness (9.3). Both sit at the same price level, but Secrets delivers a quieter, more polished experience while Dreams trades that refinement for family infrastructure. If you want a lively Puerto Vallarta family all-inclusive with kids programming, teen club, pool slides, diving, and babysitting, go to Dreams Vallarta Bay. If you want a serene adults-only Mexican resort with a golf course, superior beach and pool ratings, and a more refined atmosphere near Cancún, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a Puerto Vallarta all-inclusive with a kids club, teen club, pool slide, babysitting, diving, and fishing, and who prioritize service and cleanliness over beach or pool quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who want a polished, adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with a golf course, top-rated beach, pool, and sleep quality, and consistently high service scores in a quieter Cancún-area setting.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is minimal and humidity is lower. Puerto Vallarta's shoulder months of May and November offer good value before and after peak season. Punta Sam near Cancún shares the Yucatán's peak winter window; avoid late summer through October when Caribbean hurricane risk is at its highest.","activities":"At Dreams Vallarta Bay, guests can dive, fish, play tennis, use the pool slide, and enjoy evening entertainment and a nightclub in the heart of Puerto Vallarta, with the city's restaurants, art galleries, and Malecón boardwalk nearby. At Secrets Playa Mujeres, guests can play golf on-site, swim in heated pools, use the spa and tennis courts, and take day trips to Isla Mujeres or Cancún's hotel zone just a short ferry or drive away."},"dreams-riviera-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Riviera Cancun and Secrets Playa Mujeres share the same overall rating of 8.8, but differ meaningfully across several categories. Secrets edges ahead on beach (7.5 vs 4.8), pool (8.0 vs 7.1), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.4), room (9.0 vs 8.7), cleanliness (9.3 vs 9.1), service (9.2 vs 9.0), and sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.6), reflecting its adults-only positioning near Playa Mujeres. It also adds a golf course and tennis. Dreams counters with an extensive family infrastructure — kids club, teen club, lazy river, pool slide, diving, babysitting, and a kids club for under-4s — that Secrets simply doesn't offer. Dreams scores slightly better on value (8.5 vs 8.6, essentially tied) despite its more modest beach rating. If you want a polished adults-only Mexican resort near Cancun with superior beach, rooms, and a golf course, choose Secrets. If you want a full-featured family all-inclusive in Puerto Morelos with water features, diving, and programming for all ages, choose Dreams.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a well-rounded Mexican all-inclusive with a kids club for toddlers through teens, a lazy river, pool slide, diving, babysitting, and evening entertainment — all without needing to book restaurant reservations in advance.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples and groups who want a quieter, more refined adults-only resort near Cancun with higher-rated rooms, beach, and service, plus a golf course and tennis, in a location that consistently outperforms on sleep quality and atmosphere.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's Yucatan dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is minimal and humidity is lower. Peak weeks around Christmas and spring break push prices up at both properties. May through November brings warmer water and lower rates but increased humidity and hurricane-season risk, with September and October carrying the highest storm probability for both locations.","activities":"Both resorts offer swim-up bars, spas, gyms, evening entertainment, and nightclubs. Secrets adds golf and tennis on site. Dreams offers scuba diving, a lazy river, and water slide. Both are well positioned for excursions to nearby Mayan ruins at Tulum and Cobá, cenote swimming, snorkelling in the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef, and day trips into Cancun's hotel zone or the Isla Mujeres ferry terminal."},"breathless-riviera-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Riviera Cancun and Secrets Playa Mujeres are both adults-only Mexican all-inclusives at the same price tier with identical overall scores of 8.8, but the ratings diverge sharply in several areas. Secrets outperforms on beach (7.5 vs. 4.8), a significant gap that reflects Breathless's notably weak shoreline in the Caracol area. Secrets also leads on service (9.2 vs. 8.9), sleep quality (9.1 vs. 8.4), cleanliness (9.3 vs. 9.1), atmosphere (8.0 vs. 7.4), food (8.0 vs. 7.6), and room quality (9.0 vs. 8.9). Breathless edges ahead only on value (8.4 vs. 8.6 goes to Secrets) and location familiarity for Cancun-area travelers. Secrets adds a full golf course and tennis courts that Breathless lacks. For guests who prioritize a genuine beach experience, better food, quieter sleep, and refined service, Secrets is the stronger choice despite the longer transfer from Cancun airport. Breathless suits those who want the Cancun energy and a lively, party-forward atmosphere even at the cost of a weak beach.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a lively, nightclub-driven all-inclusive closer to the Cancun hotel zone and are willing to trade a weak beach for an energetic social atmosphere, solid room quality, and strong value at a four-dollar-sign price point.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults who want a quieter, more polished all-inclusive with a genuinely good beach, superior service ratings, golf, tennis, and a higher overall refinement level, and who do not mind the longer transfer to the Playa Mujeres area north of Cancun.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in the Mexican Caribbean, so timing is similar. December through April delivers dry, sunny weather and peak pricing. May and June offer a shoulder-season value window before hurricane season intensifies. July through October carries higher storm risk, with September the most active month. Secrets Playa Mujeres, set on a more sheltered lagoon-facing coastline, can feel slightly calmer during windy winter nortes that roughen the open Cancun coastline near Breathless.","activities":"Both properties offer heated pools with swim-up bars, spa services, gyms, evening entertainment, and nightclubs. Secrets adds an 18-hole golf course and tennis courts on-site. Nearby, guests can explore the Isla Mujeres day trip by ferry, snorkel Mesoamerican Reef sites, visit Chichen Itza or Tulum on excursions, swim in cenotes, or take a whale shark tour from Playa Mujeres during summer season. The Cancun hotel zone's shopping and dining are more accessible from Breathless."},"dreams-aventuras-riviera-maya-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Aventuras Riviera Maya is a family-focused all-inclusive in Puerto Aventuras with a waterpark, kids club for under-4s, arcade, babysitting, diving, and rooms for five or more guests. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only resort in Punta Sam near Cancún with a golf course, nightclub, tennis, and a noticeably stronger set of ratings across food (8.0 vs 7.0), beach (7.5 vs 5.3), pool (8.0 vs 6.6), atmosphere (8.0 vs 6.9), cleanliness (9.3 vs 8.9), and sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.6). Dreams Aventuras edges ahead only on value (8.7 vs 8.6) and service (9.0 vs 9.2, essentially tied). The beach gap of 2.2 points is the starkest difference and likely the single biggest factor for beach-focused travelers. Dreams is a strong family resort with excellent service and cleanliness; Secrets delivers a more polished, quieter adult experience with better food, a proper beach, and a golf course on its doorstep.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages, including toddlers, who want a well-run Mexican all-inclusive with a waterpark, kids club, babysitting, diving, and large family rooms, and who prioritize service and value over a premium beach or food program.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who want a quieter, more refined adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with a significantly better beach and food program, golf on-site, a nightclub, and top-tier cleanliness and sleep quality near Cancún.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit along Mexico's Caribbean coast, so timing is similar. December through April is peak dry season with the best weather and highest prices. Hurricane season runs June through November, with September and October carrying the most risk. Shoulder months of May and early December offer a balance of reasonable weather and lower rates at both properties.","activities":"At Dreams Aventuras, guests can dive and snorkel directly from the resort, use the waterpark, join yoga classes, and explore the Puerto Aventuras marina village next door. At Secrets Playa Mujeres, guests can play golf on the on-site course, take tennis lessons, and access Isla Mujeres by ferry for snorkeling, golf carts, and local seafood restaurants just a short ride away."},"dreams-rose-hall-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Rose Hall is a mid-price Jamaican family all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a kids club, teen club, babysitting, lazy river, nightclub, and rooms accommodating five or more guests. Secrets Playa Mujeres is a premium adults-only Mexican resort in Punta Sam with a heated pool, golf course, and ratings that consistently outpace Dreams across every measured category. Secrets scores higher on food (8.0 vs 7.4), beach (7.5 vs 6.0), pool (8.0 vs 7.1), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.1), room (9.0 vs 8.2), cleanliness (9.3 vs 8.7), service (9.2 vs 8.7), and sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.5), and comes in at a significantly higher price tier. Dreams trades in value and family infrastructure; Secrets trades in polish, quiet, and a measurably superior physical product. If you want a Jamaican family all-inclusive with kids programming, a lazy river, and large-group rooms at a wallet-friendly price, go to Dreams Rose Hall. If you want a refined, adults-only Mexican resort where nearly every quality metric is best-in-class and a premium price is justified, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a Jamaican all-inclusive with a kids club, teen club, babysitting, lazy river, and large rooms sleeping five or more, all at a mid-market price point in convenient proximity to Montego Bay.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples and pairs who want a high-end, adults-only Mexican resort where cleanliness, service, sleep quality, and room comfort all rate exceptionally well, and where a golf course and heated pool round out a premium, child-free experience.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak in the December-to-April dry season. Jamaica's Montego Bay can see rain and humidity from May through November, with hurricane risk peaking September-October. Mexico's Punta Sam area near Cancún shares a similar hurricane window. Shoulder months of May and November offer lower rates at both properties with generally manageable weather.","activities":"Dreams Rose Hall guests can play golf on-site, take to the lazy river, use the tennis courts, and explore Montego Bay's historic Hip Strip, Dunn's River Falls, and river-tubing excursions nearby. Secrets Playa Mujeres guests have access to on-site golf, a spa, and evening entertainment, plus easy access to Isla Mujeres by ferry, Cancún's dining scene, and snorkelling along the Mesoamerican Reef."},"secrets-baby-beach-aruba-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Baby Beach Aruba is a compact adults-only all-inclusive on Aruba's quieter southeastern tip near San Nicolas, distinguished by an exceptional room score (9.4) and the highest cleanliness rating of the two (9.5), but with a leaner amenity set: gym, buffet, spa, and open-seating restaurants. Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is a larger, premium adults-only property on Mexico's Isla Mujeres channel near Cancún, carrying a higher overall rating (8.8 vs 8.6) and a notably better location score (8.9 vs 8.4), with a fuller amenity roster including a golf course, heated pool, swim-up bar, tennis, nightclub, and evening entertainment. Where Baby Beach wins is in rooms, cleanliness, and service (9.3 vs 9.2), delivering an intimate, high-quality stay. Playa Mujeres trades that intimacy for a broader activity program and a more connected location near Cancún. Baby Beach scores higher on beach (8.5 vs 7.5), a meaningful gap worth noting for beach-priority travelers.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or solo travelers who prioritize an exceptionally appointed, spotlessly clean room, a reliably calm and uncrowded beach, and a relaxed low-key atmosphere on Aruba's sunny, wind-protected southern coast without needing a packed activity calendar.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults who want a full-featured luxury all-inclusive near Cancún with golf, a swim-up bar, nightclub, tennis, and evening entertainment, and who value a well-connected location for day trips to Isla Mujeres or Cancún over a top-tier beach rating.","whenToVisit":"Aruba sits outside the hurricane belt, making Baby Beach a reliable year-round destination with near-constant sunshine and trade winds keeping temperatures comfortable. Playa Mujeres is best visited November through April to avoid Mexico's Caribbean hurricane season and peak summer humidity. Both properties see higher rates and occupancy over major US holidays; shoulder months like May or late October offer better value at Playa Mujeres specifically.","activities":"Baby Beach guests can explore San Nicolas's emerging art district, snorkel the protected southeastern coves, and take day trips to Arikok National Park or Aruba's famous Natural Pool. Playa Mujeres guests have on-site golf, tennis, and a swim-up bar, plus easy access to Isla Mujeres by ferry, the Cancún hotel zone, cenote diving, and Mayan archaeological sites like El Meco within short driving distance."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-riviera-cancun-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort and Secrets Riviera Cancun are both adults-only Mexican all-inclusives at the same price tier, but meaningful rating gaps separate them. Playa Mujeres scores notably higher on beach (7.5 vs 4.8), pool (8.0 vs 7.1), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.5), and location (8.9 vs 8.2), while overall scores differ by 0.2 (8.8 vs 8.6). Playa Mujeres also adds a golf course, heated pool, and tennis courts not found at Riviera Cancun. The beach gap is the starkest differentiator: Playa Mujeres sits on a calmer, more protected stretch of coastline that guests rate nearly three points higher than Riviera Cancun's beach. Food scores also favor Playa Mujeres (8.0 vs 7.7). If you want a superior beach, an on-site golf course, a heated pool, and a stronger overall package in a quieter Punta Sam setting, choose Playa Mujeres. If proximity to Cancun's Caracol area with comparable rooms and service at a marginally lower value rating is acceptable, Riviera Cancun works.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or golf enthusiasts who want the best beach experience of the two, an on-site golf course, heated pool, and tennis courts in a quieter, more secluded Punta Sam location that earns top marks for atmosphere, cleanliness, and room quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults who prioritize room comfort and service above beach or pool quality, and want a Cancun-area adults-only base in Caracol with a spa, nightclub, and evening entertainment at a slightly more accessible overall rating.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's Caribbean coast dry season, running December through April, when rainfall is minimal and humidity manageable. July and August bring peak heat and crowds. Hurricane season peaks September through October, which carries weather risk at both properties. For the best combination of price, weather, and availability, target late November or early May as shoulder-season sweet spots.","activities":"Guests at Playa Mujeres can play on-site golf, use tennis courts, and access a heated pool alongside standard swim-up bar and beach amenities. Nearby, the Isla Mujeres ferry offers a short day trip for snorkelling, golf cart exploration, and seafood. Riviera Cancun guests are closer to Cancun's hotel zone, putting the Nichupté Lagoon, Zona Hotelera nightlife, and cenote day trips within easy reach of both resorts."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-marigot-bay-st-lucia":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only Mexican all-inclusive on the Punta Sam coast north of Cancún, with a golf course, heated pool, nightclub, tennis, evening entertainment, and a strong beach rating of 7.5, earning an overall 8.8 across polished rooms (9.0) and exceptional cleanliness (9.3). Zoëtry Marigot Bay St. Lucia is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive tucked into the dramatic hillside of Marigot Bay, where the jungle-meets-marina setting earns atmosphere and food ratings of 8.6 each, but the beach scores a stark 2.5 and the pool lags at 7.4. Secrets wins decisively on beach, pool, and breadth of amenities, including golf and nightlife, while Zoëtry counters with better food, equivalent service (9.1), and a genuinely striking St. Lucian setting that prioritises atmosphere over sand. At the same price tier, the choice is essentially active beach holiday in Mexico versus intimate rainforest-bay escape in the Caribbean.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or solo travellers who want a well-rounded Mexican all-inclusive with a proper beach, golf, heated pool, nightclub, and polished service north of Cancún, all at a price point that delivers strong value ratings without sacrificing room quality or cleanliness.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples drawn to St. Lucia's dramatic scenery who prioritise exceptional food, a tranquil boutique atmosphere, and the visual spectacle of Marigot Bay over beach access, and who are comfortable trading sand and nightlife for hillside seclusion and superior dining.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Playa Mujeres benefits from Mexico's dry season, December through April, when the Caribbean coast sees minimal rain and calm seas. Zoëtry Marigot Bay sits in St. Lucia's drier corridor but still experiences a wetter season June through November; January through April offers the most reliable sunshine. Both resorts are in peak demand over the Christmas and New Year period, so book early for either if travelling over the holidays.","activities":"Secrets guests can golf on-site, play tennis, swim from the beach or heated pool, and fill evenings at the nightclub and entertainment program. Zoëtry guests lack comparable on-site breadth but can fish from the bay, explore Marigot Bay's marina village, arrange excursions to the Pitons, and access St. Lucia's hiking and whale-watching. Neither resort is near a major activity hub, but St. Lucia's island excursions offer more natural spectacle than the Punta Sam coastline."},"breathless-montego-bay-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Montego Bay and Secrets Playa Mujeres are both adults-only, upper-upscale all-inclusives, but the ratings tell a clear story: Secrets outscores Breathless across nearly every category. The gap is most pronounced in cleanliness (9.3 vs. 8.9), service (9.2 vs. 8.7), room quality (9.0 vs. 8.7), sleep quality (9.1 vs. 8.3), and beach (7.5 vs. 5.5), which is Breathless's weakest score by a wide margin. Secrets also edges ahead on overall rating (8.8 vs. 8.5) and value (8.6 vs. 8.3). The most meaningful differentiator beyond ratings is the golf course at Secrets, which is a genuine draw for golfers who want to stay all-inclusive. Breathless counters with a livelier nightclub-driven atmosphere and a strong Montego Bay location score (8.5), appealing to guests who want an energetic, socially oriented Jamaican resort. If the beach is a priority, Secrets wins decisively. If nightlife energy and Jamaica's culture are the draw, Breathless holds its own.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a lively, socially driven adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive with a strong nightclub scene and Montego Bay's cultural backdrop, and who are less concerned about beach quality or pristine resort polish.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults and couples who prioritize top-tier service, immaculate cleanliness, excellent sleep quality, and a superior beach, with the added bonus of on-site golf in a quieter, more refined Mexican resort setting near Cancún.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations are best visited between December and April when rainfall is lowest and humidity is manageable. Jamaica's peak season runs December through mid-April; the Yucatán peninsula around Playa Mujeres shares a similar peak window. Both carry hurricane season risk from June through November, with September and October the riskiest months in each location.","activities":"At Breathless Montego Bay, guests can explore Hip Strip dining and bars, take excursions to Dunn's River Falls, or arrange ATV and catamaran tours nearby. At Secrets Playa Mujeres, the on-site golf course is the standout, supplemented by snorkelling excursions, trips to Isla Mujeres by ferry, and Cancún day trips just 30 minutes away. Both resorts offer spa treatments, tennis, swim-up bars, and evening entertainment on property."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-wild-orchid-montego-bay":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only Mexican all-inclusive on the Punta Sam peninsula near Isla Mujeres, with an on-site golf course, heated pool, spa, and no-reservation dining in a quieter, more secluded setting. Secrets Wild Orchid Montego Bay is an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a casino, lazy river, diving, and room service in a livelier, more urban resort corridor. Playa Mujeres scores notably higher on pool (8.0 vs 7.2), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.7), beach (7.5 vs 6.8), rooms (9.0 vs 8.9), cleanliness (9.3 vs 9.0), service (9.2 vs 8.9), and overall rating (8.8 vs 8.6). Wild Orchid counters with a casino, lazy river, diving program, and room service that Playa Mujeres lacks, plus paid Wi-Fi versus free at Playa Mujeres. Playa Mujeres suits guests who prioritize a refined, secluded setting with golf and superior pool and beach ratings, while Wild Orchid suits those who want Jamaican energy, a casino, and watersports variety.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples and golf enthusiasts who want a polished, secluded Mexican resort with high marks for cleanliness, service, and rooms, a heated pool, on-site golf course, and a quieter atmosphere away from a busy resort strip.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults-only couples who want a lively Jamaican all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a casino, lazy river, diving program, and room service, and who value Caribbean cultural energy alongside a full suite of nightlife and watersport options.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in peak demand from December through April when Caribbean and Mexican weather is driest and most settled. Mexico's Punta Sam peninsula sees its best conditions November through May. Jamaica's Montego Bay is drier January through April. Both destinations can experience Atlantic hurricane activity from June through November, with September and October carrying the highest risk at both properties.","activities":"At Playa Mujeres, guests can play the on-site golf course, take the ferry to Isla Mujeres, snorkel the nearby reefs, or explore Cancun's Zona Hotelera. At Wild Orchid, guests can dive with the resort's on-site program, tour the Montego Bay Marine Park, visit Rose Hall Great House, or explore Montego Bay's Hip Strip. Both resorts offer spa treatments, tennis, swim-up bars, and evening entertainment on property."},"dreams-playa-esmeralda-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Playa Esmeralda and Secrets Playa Mujeres share an identical cleanliness score (9.3), service (9.2), and sleep quality (9.1), but diverge sharply in concept and guest profile. Dreams is a family resort in the Dominican Republic's El Cedro area, scoring a standout 9.2 on rooms and 9 on location, with a kids club, teen club, babysitting, and under-4 programming built into its offering. Secrets Playa Mujeres is adults-only on Mexico's Punta Sam peninsula, and outperforms Dreams on food (8.0 vs 7.6), pool (8.0 vs 7.1), and atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.5), while adding a golf course, swim-up bar, nightclub, heated pool, and tennis. Dreams counters with a higher beach score (8.3 vs 7.5) and a slightly higher overall rating (8.9 vs 8.8). If you want a Dominican Republic family all-inclusive with strong room quality, an excellent beach, and full kids programming, go to Dreams Playa Esmeralda. If you want an adults-only Mexican resort with better food, a golf course, nightclub, and a more polished social atmosphere, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages, including toddlers, who want a high-quality Dominican Republic all-inclusive with strong rooms, a superior beach score, dedicated kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and no reservation hassle at restaurants.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples and groups who want a refined, amenity-rich Mexican all-inclusive with golf, a nightclub, swim-up bar, heated pool, and better food and atmosphere ratings, without children in the mix.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Playa Esmeralda benefits from the Dominican Republic's dry season, December through April, when rainfall is minimal and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Secrets Playa Mujeres sits near Cancun, where peak season runs November through April, avoiding the June-to-October hurricane window. Both resorts carry elevated pricing in the Christmas and New Year period.","activities":"Dreams guests can enjoy the beach, spa, gym, and a full kids and teen programming schedule, with excursions to nearby El Cedro and broader Dominican Republic attractions accessible from the resort. Secrets Playa Mujeres guests can play golf on the on-site course, hit the tennis courts, snorkel, use the swim-up bar, catch evening entertainment, and access Isla Mujeres and Cancun's nightlife and cenotes nearby."},"breathless-cancun-soul-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Cancun Soul Resort & Spa is an adults-only all-inclusive in Puerto Morelos with a nightclub, swim-up bar, evening entertainment, and a party-forward atmosphere, posting strong room (9.1) and cleanliness (9.3) scores but softer marks for food (7.6), pool (7.4), and atmosphere (7.5). Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only all-inclusive in Punta Sam that outscores Breathless on nearly every metric: food (8.0 vs 7.6), pool (8.0 vs 7.4), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.5), service (9.2 vs 8.8), sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.5), value (8.6 vs 8.3), and overall (8.8 vs 8.4). Secrets also adds a golf course and tennis courts, and its no-reservation restaurant policy removes friction from dining. The beach score at Breathless edges ahead slightly (7.8 vs 7.5). Both are the same price tier, making Secrets the stronger all-round performer, while Breathless appeals more to guests prioritizing nightlife energy and a livelier social scene.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a high-energy, nightlife-driven all-inclusive on the Mexican Caribbean with a nightclub and swim-up bar as focal points. Best for younger couples or groups who prioritize a lively social atmosphere and don't mind softer food and pool scores in exchange for the party vibe.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults and couples who want a more refined, well-rounded adults-only experience with superior service (9.2), excellent sleep quality (9.1), no-reservation dining, and a golf course on-site. Ideal for those who want to feel genuinely looked after and have more activity options beyond the beach and bar.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit on Mexico's Caribbean coast and share the same seasonal logic. December through April offers dry, sunny weather with lower humidity and the best sea conditions. May through November brings heat, humidity, and hurricane-season risk, with September and October the most vulnerable months. Shoulder periods in late November or early May offer a balance of good weather and lower rates at both properties.","activities":"At Breathless, guests gravitate toward swim-up bar sessions, beach time, evening entertainment, and the nightclub. Secrets Playa Mujeres layers in golf on its on-site course and tennis courts alongside the same beach, pool, and nightclub offerings. Both properties sit near Cancun and Isla Mujeres, giving guests access to snorkelling, diving at the Mesoamerican Reef, Isla Mujeres ferry trips, cenote excursions, and Mayan ruins at Chichen Itza or Tulum."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-st-james-montego-bay":{"keyDifferences":"Both are adults-only, $$$$-priced all-inclusives sharing the same location score (8.9), but Secrets Playa Mujeres pulls ahead on nearly every other metric. Its overall rating is 8.8 versus 8.5, with a notably higher pool score (8.0 vs 7.2), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.7), and room quality (9.0 vs 8.8). Cleanliness and service are both stronger at Playa Mujeres (9.3 and 9.2 vs 9.0 and 8.9). The beach score gap is significant: 7.5 at Playa Mujeres against a weak 6.8 at St. James. Playa Mujeres sits on Mexico's Isla Mujeres corridor and adds a full golf course and spa, while Secrets St. James is a Montego Bay adults-only property that counters with a casino and on-site diving. If you want a higher-rated Mexican adults-only resort with a golf course, superior pool experience, and stronger across-the-board ratings, go to Playa Mujeres. If you want an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a casino and diving program, go to Secrets St. James.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples and golfers who want a premium Mexican adults-only all-inclusive with a full golf course, spa, and top-tier ratings across rooms, service, and cleanliness in a quieter location away from the main Cancun strip.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples who prioritize a Jamaican setting and want casino access and on-site diving alongside the standard adults-only all-inclusive formula, and who are comfortable with lower pool and beach scores than comparable Mexican alternatives.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when rainfall is minimal. Mexico's Playa Mujeres can see hurricane disruption June through October, as can Jamaica. Montego Bay's shoulder seasons (May, November) offer lower rates with manageable weather. Playa Mujeres benefits from slightly more consistent winds off the Caribbean coast, making late spring visits comfortable before the rainy season sets in.","activities":"Playa Mujeres guests can golf on-site, take day trips to Isla Mujeres by ferry, snorkel, or explore Cancun's Zona Hotelera. Secrets St. James guests can dive on-site, visit Montego Bay's Hip Strip, take excursions to Dunn's River Falls, or explore the Blue Mountains. Both resorts offer tennis, spa treatments, swim-up bars, and evening entertainment programs within the property."},"dreams-sands-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Sands Cancun is a family all-inclusive on Cancun's main hotel zone with a kids club, lazy river, and infant-specific programming for under-4s, rated 8.5 overall. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only resort in the quieter Punta Sam area north of Cancun, rated higher across nearly every metric: food 8.0 vs 6.9, pool 8.0 vs 6.0, beach 7.5 vs 6.5, atmosphere 8.0 vs 6.7, room 9.0 vs 7.8, cleanliness 9.3 vs 8.5, and service 9.2 vs 8.7. Secrets also adds a golf course, spa, heated pool, swim-up bar, nightclub, and tennis. The gap in food and pool ratings is especially stark. Dreams wins on Cancun's central location and family infrastructure; Secrets wins on almost every quality measure in a more secluded, adults-only setting. If you want a family-focused Cancun all-inclusive with young-child amenities and a central hotel zone address, choose Dreams Sands. If you want a higher-quality adults-only Mexican resort with golf, spa, and substantially better food, rooms, and service, choose Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children, including infants, who want a centrally located Cancun all-inclusive with a kids club, lazy river, and easy access to Cancun's hotel zone attractions without needing restaurant reservations.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups seeking a premium, tranquil Mexican resort experience with golf, spa, a heated pool, and standout service and cleanliness scores, willing to stay slightly outside central Cancun for a markedly elevated all-inclusive quality.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Cancun's peak dry season, December through April, when rainfall is minimal and temperatures are pleasant in the low-to-mid 80s. Avoid hurricane season, particularly September and October. Secrets Playa Mujeres' more secluded Punta Sam location feels especially worthwhile in the quieter shoulder months of May and November, when crowds thin and value improves.","activities":"Both resorts offer beach access and dining without reservations. Dreams Sands adds a lazy river and kids club programming. Secrets Playa Mujeres layers in an on-site golf course, spa, tennis, swim-up bar, and nightclub. Nearby, guests at either resort can access Isla Mujeres day trips, Cancun's shopping and nightlife, cenote excursions, and Chichen Itza tours, all easily arranged through resort concierge services."},"dreams-sapphire-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Sapphire Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Puerto Morelos with a kids club, teen club, babysitting, diving, snorkelling, fishing, yoga, and a nightclub at a busy stretch of the Riviera Maya. Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only all-inclusive in Punta Sam near Isla Mujeres with a golf course, heated pool, and a consistently superior ratings profile across nearly every category. Secrets outscores Dreams on food by a significant 0.8 points (8.0 vs 7.2), beach by 2.5 points (7.5 vs 5.0), pool by 1.3 points (8.0 vs 6.7), room by 0.5 points (9.0 vs 8.5), cleanliness by 0.5 points (9.3 vs 8.8), and sleep quality by 0.6 points (9.1 vs 8.5). Dreams holds an edge in service (9.0 vs 9.2 for Secrets) and offers the family-specific infrastructure Secrets entirely lacks. If you want a family-friendly Mexican all-inclusive with dedicated kids programming, diving, and snorkelling, go to Dreams Sapphire. If you want a polished, adults-only Mexican resort with on-site golf, superior food, and a quieter atmosphere, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a well-serviced Mexican all-inclusive with a kids club, teen club, babysitting, water activities including diving and snorkelling, and evening entertainment in a Riviera Maya setting.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who want a refined, adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with on-site golf, a heated pool, superior food ratings, and exceptional cleanliness and sleep quality in a quieter location near Isla Mujeres.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula dry season, running December through April, when humidity is lower and rainfall minimal. July and August are warm and busy with families at Dreams Sapphire. Hurricane season peaks September through October, when rates drop at both properties but weather risk increases. Secrets Playa Mujeres suits shoulder season travel for couples seeking quieter, better-value stays.","activities":"Dreams Sapphire guests can dive, snorkel, fish, and kayak directly from the resort, with Puerto Morelos's protected reef nearby. Both resorts offer tennis, spa treatments, swim-up bars, and evening entertainment. Secrets Playa Mujeres adds on-site golf as a major draw. Guests at either property can arrange excursions to Chichen Itza, Tulum ruins, cenote swims, and the colorful Isla Mujeres, which is particularly convenient from Secrets Playa Mujeres."},"secrets-mirabel-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Mirabel Cancún and Secrets Playa Mujeres are both adults-only, same-price-tier Mexican all-inclusives with nearly identical overall ratings (8.7 vs 8.8) and matching scores for atmosphere (8.0), value (8.6), and cleanliness (9.3). The real distinctions are in amenities and location feel. Mirabel sits in Cancún proper, earning a location score of 9.0 versus Playa Mujeres' 8.9, with easier access to the Hotel Zone's nightlife and attractions. Its room score edges slightly higher at 9.1 versus 9.0. Playa Mujeres, set on the quieter Punta Sam peninsula north of Cancún, counters with a better pool score (8.0 vs 7.5), a heated pool, a full golf course, tennis courts, a nightclub, and restaurants that require no reservations — a meaningfully larger amenity set. Playa Mujeres also scores marginally better on beach (7.5 vs 7.3) and service (9.2 vs 9.1). Mirabel suits guests who want urban convenience; Playa Mujeres suits those who want a self-contained, activity-rich resort in a more secluded coastal setting.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a polished Cancún all-inclusive with outstanding rooms and sleep quality (9.1, 9.2) and easy access to the Hotel Zone's restaurants, shopping, and nightlife. Best for couples or solo travelers who plan to explore beyond the resort and want a strong location score to back that up.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults who prefer a larger, more self-contained resort experience away from Cancún's busier strip. Ideal for golfers, tennis players, and anyone who wants a heated pool, nightclub, and no-reservation dining in a quieter, more secluded Punta Sam setting without sacrificing service quality (9.2).","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from the same regional climate. December through April offers dry, sunny weather and peak-season pricing. May and June are warm and less crowded before hurricane season intensifies. July and August see higher humidity and occasional storms but better rates. September and October carry the highest storm risk and the deepest discounts across both properties.","activities":"At Mirabel, guests can snorkel directly from the resort, use the spa and gym, and take short trips into Cancún's Hotel Zone for shopping, cenotes, and Isla Mujeres day trips. Playa Mujeres adds on-site golf and tennis, and its quieter location makes it a base for Isla Mujeres ferry crossings and nearby nature reserves. Both properties offer spa treatments, swim-up bar access, and evening entertainment programs."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-sunscape-dorado-pacifico-ixtapa":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only luxury all-inclusive on Mexico's Punta Sam coast, rated 8.8 overall with standout scores for cleanliness (9.3), service (9.2), sleep quality (9.1), and rooms (9.0), and a full amenity set including a golf course, spa, heated pool, swim-up bar, nightclub, and multiple restaurants requiring no reservations. Sunscape Dorado Pacifico Ixtapa is a family all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast priced a tier lower, rated 8.6 overall but with noticeably weaker scores across food (6.4 vs 8.0), pool (6.2 vs 8.0), atmosphere (6.3 vs 8.0), and beach (6.8 vs 7.5). Sunscape's amenity list is sparse by comparison, with beach access listed as its only confirmed facility. Secrets earns its premium price through superior service, immaculate rooms, and a rich activity lineup in a tranquil adults-only setting. Sunscape offers solid value and a family-friendly Pacific Coast location at a lower price point, but guests should expect meaningful gaps in food quality and on-site amenities relative to Secrets.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults and couples seeking a polished, high-service Mexican all-inclusive with a golf course, spa, nightclub, and consistently excellent rooms and cleanliness, and who are willing to pay a premium for a quieter, adults-only atmosphere near Cancun.","whoShouldChooseB":"Budget-conscious families who want a relaxed Pacific Coast Mexico base in Ixtapa at a lower price point and can look past weaker food and pool ratings, prioritizing location value and a laid-back family atmosphere over extensive on-site amenities.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's dry season, roughly November through April, when rain is minimal and humidity drops. Ixtapa on the Pacific side can see significant rainfall June through October during hurricane season, and while Cancun-area resorts like Secrets face similar seasonal risk, the Caribbean coast's peak dry season tends to offer more reliably calm beach conditions from December through March.","activities":"Guests at Secrets Playa Mujeres can play golf on-site, book spa treatments, use the heated pool and swim-up bar, play tennis, and access evening entertainment and a nightclub without leaving the property. Sunscape Dorado Pacifico guests are well-positioned for Ixtapa's surrounding attractions, including deep-sea fishing, crocodile sanctuary visits, snorkelling at Ixtapa Island, and exploring the lively adjacent resort town of Zihuatanejo, compensating for the resort's thinner on-site activity offering."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-sunscape-dominicus-la-romana":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only luxury all-inclusive on Mexico's Punta Sam peninsula, earning standout scores for rooms (9.0), cleanliness (9.3), service (9.2), and sleep quality (9.1), with a full amenity stack including a golf course, spa, heated pool, swim-up bar, nightclub, tennis, and multiple restaurants requiring no reservations. Sunscape Dominicus La Romana is a family all-inclusive on the Dominican Republic's southern coast, where the beach rating (8.0) is its strongest suit, but food (6.2), pool (6.2), and atmosphere (6.2) ratings trail Secrets by significant margins. Secrets scores 0.7 points higher overall (8.8 vs 8.1) despite both sitting at the same price level, making it the considerably stronger value proposition for non-families. Sunscape's advantage is purely structural: kids clubs, a teen club, and waterparks for both age groups make it a workable family destination. If you want a polished, amenity-rich adults-only Mexican resort with exceptional rooms and service, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres. If you want a family-focused Dominican all-inclusive with waterpark facilities and a good beach, go to Sunscape Dominicus.","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples and adult groups seeking a premium adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with exceptional service (9.2), immaculate rooms (9.0), a golf course, spa, and full evening entertainment program at a price point that genuinely delivers on its luxury positioning.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of varying ages who prioritize dedicated kids infrastructure — a kids club, teen club, and two waterparks — over food or pool quality, and who want a decent Dominican beach without paying a premium for adult-oriented amenities they won't use.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations offer year-round Caribbean warmth. Mexico's Punta Sam peninsula is driest and calmest November through April, avoiding peak hurricane risk. The Dominican Republic's La Romana coast similarly favors November through April. Both carry hurricane exposure June through October, though La Romana sits in a somewhat more sheltered southern position. Shoulder months of May and November offer better pricing at both properties.","activities":"Secrets Playa Mujeres guests can golf on-site, take spa treatments, play tennis, snorkel the calm Isla Mujeres channel, or ferry across to Isla Mujeres town for shopping and seafood. Sunscape Dominicus guests can explore the nearby Altos de Chavón artists' village, take river excursions through La Romana's Chavón canyon, visit Casa de Campo's polo grounds, or arrange day trips to Bayahibe for reef snorkelling."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-tulum-resort-and-beach-club":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort and Secrets Tulum Resort & Beach Club are both adults-only Mexican all-inclusives at the same price tier, but they differ meaningfully across several key ratings. Playa Mujeres scores higher overall (8.8 vs 8.3), on beach (7.5 vs 5.5, a significant 2-point gap), location (8.9 vs 7.8), value (8.6 vs 7.9), and service (9.2 vs 8.8). Tulum edges ahead only on atmosphere (8.5 vs 8.0), reflecting its jungle-chic aesthetic and bohemian setting. Playa Mujeres is the more amenity-rich property, offering a golf course, spa, swim-up bar, gym, tennis, nightclub, heated pool, and evening entertainment on a calm, accessible stretch north of Cancún. Secrets Tulum has a stripped-back amenity list with no gym, no golf, no nightclub, and a notably weaker beach score, leaning instead on the cultural pull of the Tulum corridor. If you want a full-featured adults-only resort with a strong beach and on-site golf near Cancún, choose Playa Mujeres. If you want a design-forward jungle atmosphere and proximity to Tulum's cenotes and ruins, choose Tulum.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults and couples who want a polished, amenity-rich all-inclusive with on-site golf, a spa, nightclub, and a solid beach experience in a quieter location north of Cancún, where high service scores (9.2) and strong value (8.6) justify the premium price.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults drawn to Tulum's bohemian, jungle-chic aesthetic who prioritize atmosphere (8.5) and beautifully designed rooms (8.9) over beach quality and a full amenity lineup, and who plan to spend time exploring cenotes, Mayan ruins, and the Tulum hotel zone.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's dry season, roughly December through April, when humidity is lower and rainfall minimal. Playa Mujeres, being closer to Cancún, can see stronger northerly winds (nortes) in winter that occasionally affect the beach. Tulum's jungle setting means higher humidity year-round, and the wet season from June through October brings afternoon rains. Either resort is best avoided during peak hurricane season, August through October.","activities":"Playa Mujeres guests can play the on-site golf course, use the tennis courts, and access Cancún's attractions and the Isla Mujeres ferry nearby. Tulum guests are steps from some of Mexico's most iconic cenotes, the Cobá and Tulum Mayan ruins, and the Sian Ka'an Biosphere Reserve. Both resorts are in Mexico's Riviera Maya corridor, making day trips to Chichen Itza, Akumal sea turtle snorkeling, and Playa del Carmen feasible from either property."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-montego-bay-jamaica":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres and Zoëtry Montego Bay are both adults-only luxury all-inclusives at the same price tier, but their ratings and amenities reveal meaningful gaps. Secrets scores higher across nearly every dimension: overall (8.8 vs 8.2), pool (8.0 vs 6.7), location (8.9 vs 8.1), value (8.6 vs 7.9), and cleanliness (9.3 vs 8.9). The beach gap is the starkest differentiator — Secrets rates 7.5 while Zoëtry scores a very weak 4.0, making the Jamaican property a poor choice for beach-focused travelers. Secrets adds a full golf course, heated pool, swim-up bar, tennis, nightclub, and evening entertainment — a significantly broader amenity set. Zoëtry's strengths are narrower: room quality is close (8.7 vs 9.0), service is strong (8.8), and its Montego Bay setting suits guests who want proximity to Jamaica's cultural scene rather than resort-centric activity. If you want a well-rounded Mexican adults-only resort with excellent beach access, golf, and lively amenities, choose Secrets. If you want an intimate Jamaican retreat and can accept a weak beach and pool product, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples and solo travelers who want a polished, amenity-rich Mexican all-inclusive with golf, a swim-up bar, evening entertainment, and a genuine beach — all backed by outstanding cleanliness (9.3) and service (9.2) scores at a price point that delivers strong value.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults-only couples who prioritize a quiet, intimate atmosphere and excellent sleep quality (8.9) over a strong beach or pool product, and who want to be close enough to Montego Bay to explore Jamaica's food, culture, and music scene beyond the resort gates.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April for dry, sunny weather. Mexico's Punta Sam area avoids hurricane season most reliably, making it a safer bet from August through October. Jamaica's Montego Bay sits in the Atlantic hurricane belt, with peak risk July through October, so shoulder season visits in May or November offer better pricing with lower storm risk for Zoëtry.","activities":"At Secrets Playa Mujeres, guests play golf on-site, hit the swim-up bar, join evening entertainment, or take day trips to Isla Mujeres and Cancun's cenotes nearby. At Zoëtry Montego Bay, the resort itself offers limited activity variety, but Montego Bay delivers: Dunn's River Falls, the Hip Strip, ATV tours, and river rafting on the Martha Brae are all within reach for guests willing to venture out."},"dreams-los-cabos-suites-golf-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive on Mexico's Baja Peninsula near San Jose del Cabo, with a kids club for under-4s and solid room and service scores (8.7 and 8.7), but it carries a notably weak beach rating of 3.3 and middling food score of 7.5. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only all-inclusive near Cancún on the Yucatán side, with a genuinely strong beach (7.5 vs. 3.3), superior food (8.0 vs. 7.5), and across-the-board higher scores in cleanliness (9.3 vs. 8.9), service (9.2 vs. 8.7), sleep quality (9.1 vs. 8.6), and overall rating (8.8 vs. 8.6). Secrets also offers a heated pool, nightclub, gym, tennis, and evening entertainment, while Dreams leans on its Cabo location and family infrastructure. If you want a family-oriented Cabo resort with a kids club and strong room quality despite a compromised beach, choose Dreams Los Cabos. If you want a polished adults-only Caribbean-side resort with a real beach, higher service standards, and a fuller amenity set, choose Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children who prioritize the dramatic Cabo scenery, strong room quality, and a kids club for toddlers, and who can accept that the beach experience will be limited by Baja's Pacific-side surf conditions rather than calm Caribbean waters.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want a refined, adults-only Cancún-area all-inclusive with a genuine beach, top-tier cleanliness and service scores, golf on-site, and a full evening entertainment program in a quieter setting north of the main Cancún hotel zone.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Los Cabos benefits from Cabo's dry, sunny winters (November through April), avoiding the late-summer hurricane season that affects Baja. Secrets Playa Mujeres sits on the Caribbean side, where the dry season also runs November through April, keeping humidity lower and seas calmer. Both resorts share similar optimal travel windows, though Cabo's shoulder months of May and October offer particularly good value.","activities":"At Dreams Los Cabos, guests have access to Cabo San Lucas boat tours, whale watching from January through March, sport fishing, and ATV excursions into the desert. Secrets Playa Mujeres offers on-site golf, tennis, and easy ferry access to Isla Mujeres for snorkeling, golf cart tours, and exploring the island's coral reefs, with Cancún's shopping and nightlife a short drive south."},"dreams-bahia-mita-surf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Bahia Mita is a family all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast in Punta de Mita, with a kids club for under-4s, babysitting, and a surf-adjacent setting, though its beach rating is notably weak at 4.8 compared to Secrets Playa Mujeres' 7.5. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only all-inclusive near Cancun on the Caribbean side, with a golf course, heated pool, swim-up bar, nightclub, and tennis, and it outscores Dreams across nearly every measured category: food 8.0 vs 7.3, pool 8.0 vs 7.1, atmosphere 8.0 vs 7.4, service 9.2 vs 9.0, and sleep quality 9.1 vs 8.8. Both sit at the same price tier and share strong room and cleanliness scores. Dreams is the choice for families wanting Pacific Mexico with infant-friendly programming, while Secrets delivers a more polished, amenity-rich Caribbean experience for couples. If you want a Pacific Mexico family all-inclusive with a kids club and babysitting in the Punta de Mita area, go to Dreams Bahia Mita. If you want an adults-only Caribbean all-inclusive near Cancun with golf, a nightclub, and stronger ratings across food, beach, and atmosphere, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children who want a Pacific Mexico all-inclusive in the scenic Punta de Mita area, with a kids club for under-4s, babysitting, and strong room and cleanliness scores, and who can accept a weaker beach in exchange for the location.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adults who want a polished, amenity-loaded Caribbean all-inclusive near Cancun with golf, a heated pool, swim-up bar, nightclub, tennis, and consistently higher ratings across food, beach, atmosphere, and service than most competitors at this price level.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Bahia Mita on the Pacific coast is best November through April when dry season delivers reliable sunshine and calmer surf; summer brings humidity and Pacific swells. Secrets Playa Mujeres on the Caribbean side is also best December through April, avoiding the June–November hurricane season. Both properties sit in the same broad Mexican resort corridor and share a similar peak-season pricing window.","activities":"At Dreams Bahia Mita, the Pacific surf break is a draw for water-sports enthusiasts, and the Punta de Mita area offers whale watching, sport fishing, and access to the Marieta Islands. At Secrets Playa Mujeres, on-site golf, tennis, and a swim-up bar anchor the activity lineup, while the nearby Isla Mujeres ferry, Cancun's Zona Hotelera, and snorkelling along the Mesoamerican Reef add strong off-property options."},"dreams-natura-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Natura Resort & Spa is a family-friendly all-inclusive in Puerto Morelos with a kids club for under-4s and a notably high cleanliness score of 9.0, but its beach rating of 4.5 is a significant weakness, and food scores just 7.3. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only resort in Punta Sam that outperforms Dreams Natura across nearly every rated category: beach jumps to 7.5, food to 8.0, pool to 8.0, atmosphere to 8.0, service to 9.2, and sleep quality to 9.1. Room ratings are also higher at Secrets (9.0 vs 8.8). The amenity gap is equally wide — Secrets adds a golf course, spa, heated pool, swim-up bar, gym, tennis, nightclub, and evening entertainment, while Dreams Natura's amenity list is notably lean. Dreams Natura's strongest suit is its room quality and cleanliness in a family context. Secrets Playa Mujeres is simply a more complete, higher-rated resort that commands its adults-only premium. If you need a kids club, Dreams Natura is your only option here; if you don't, Secrets wins on almost every measurable metric.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children, particularly under-4s, who want a clean, comfortable Mexican all-inclusive in Puerto Morelos and can tolerate a weaker beach and a thinner amenity offering in exchange for child-friendly programming and well-rated rooms.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or adult groups who want a high-performing adults-only Mexican resort with strong scores across food, service, beach, and sleep quality, plus a full amenity suite including golf, spa, heated pool, tennis, and nightclub — all without the backdrop of young families.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is lowest and humidity manageable. July and August are busy with domestic families. Hurricane season peaks September to October, when rates drop but weather risk rises. Secrets Playa Mujeres, catering to couples, tends to attract a quieter crowd year-round compared to family resorts in high summer.","activities":"Both resorts sit near the northern Yucatan coast, giving guests access to Isla Mujeres by ferry, snorkelling in the Mesoamerican Reef, and cenote diving nearby. Secrets adds on-site golf, tennis, and a full spa. Puerto Morelos near Dreams Natura has a charming town square and a protected reef just offshore. Playa Mujeres near Secrets is quieter and more isolated, suiting guests who prefer a self-contained resort experience."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-secrets-st-lucia-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres and Secrets St. Lucia are both adults-only, upper-upscale all-inclusives at the same price tier, but their amenity sets and on-site ratings diverge significantly. Playa Mujeres scores higher on overall rating (8.8 vs 8.6), pool (8.0 vs 7.6), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.8), and room quality (9.0 vs 8.6), while both resorts tie on food (8.0), value (8.6), and service (9.2). The beach gap is notable: Playa Mujeres rates 7.5 versus St. Lucia's 6.8, though neither is a standout beach resort. Where Playa Mujeres pulls decisively ahead is amenities: it offers a golf course, heated pool, gym, spa, swim-up bar, tennis, nightclub, and evening entertainment. Secrets St. Lucia lists no comparable amenity set, making it a much more pared-back experience. If you want a full-featured Mexican adults-only resort with golf, spa, and nightlife, Playa Mujeres is the stronger option. If St. Lucia's dramatic volcanic scenery and slower Caribbean pace matter more than on-site programming, St. Lucia warrants consideration despite fewer amenities.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples and groups who want a feature-rich Mexican adults-only resort with a golf course, spa, swim-up bar, tennis, nightclub, and evening entertainment in a well-rated property near Cancun. Ideal for those who want to stay busy on-site and value high room quality and cleanliness at a competitive price.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples drawn to St. Lucia's iconic volcanic landscape and lush tropical setting who are comfortable with a quieter, amenity-light experience. Best suited to those for whom the destination itself, rather than on-site programming, is the primary draw, and who prioritize sleep quality and attentive service over activities.","whenToVisit":"Playa Mujeres benefits from Mexico's dry season, December through April, when humidity drops and rain is rare. St. Lucia's dry season runs similarly from December through May, before the Atlantic hurricane season peaks. Both destinations are at elevated weather risk from August through October. Shoulder months like November and late April offer better rates at both resorts while still catching reliable weather.","activities":"Guests at Playa Mujeres can golf on-site, take tennis lessons, use the spa, snorkel off the coast, or take a short ferry to Isla Mujeres for local restaurants and beaches. St. Lucia guests can explore the UNESCO-listed Piton Mountains, visit the drive-in volcano at Sulphur Springs, tour cocoa and banana plantations, hike the Tet Paul Nature Trail, or arrange whale-watching and sailing excursions from nearby Soufriere."},"dreams-tulum-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Tulum is a family-friendly Mexican all-inclusive on the Riviera Maya with a kids club for under-4s, a beach, and no-reservation dining at a $$$ price point, posting solid but modest ratings: overall 8.2, food 7.0, beach 6.3, and pool 6.7. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only resort near Cancun in Punta Sam with a golf course, heated pool, spa, swim-up bar, nightclub, tennis, and gym, and it outscores Dreams Tulum across every single category: overall 8.8, food 8.0, beach 7.5, pool 8.0, room 9.0, cleanliness 9.3, and service 9.2. The gaps are significant — a full point on rooms, nearly a point on cleanliness and service, and 1.2 points on beach. Dreams Tulum's main advantages are its Tulum-area location and family orientation. Secrets Playa Mujeres wins on polish, amenities breadth, and guest satisfaction at every measurable level. If you want a family-friendly Riviera Maya all-inclusive near Tulum with infant programming and a relaxed beach setting, go to Dreams Tulum. If you want a high-performing adults-only resort near Cancun with golf, a heated pool, and superior ratings across the board, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children, including infants and toddlers, who want a comfortable Riviera Maya base near Tulum with a kids club catering to under-4s, reliable service, and easy no-reservation dining without the polish premium of an adults-only resort.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who want a high-end, adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with exceptional cleanliness (9.3), outstanding rooms (9.0), golf, spa, nightclub, and a heated pool, and are willing to pay for a measurably superior resort experience near Cancun.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit on Mexico's Caribbean coast and share the same seasonal rhythms. December through April offers the driest, most reliable weather. July and August are popular but humid. September and October carry the highest hurricane risk and see the fewest visitors. Playa Mujeres, being closer to Cancun, can feel breezier in winter, which suits the heated pool at Secrets. Tulum's shoulder months of May and June offer good value with lighter crowds.","activities":"Dreams Tulum guests are well-placed to explore the famous Tulum Mayan ruins, cenote swimming at Gran Cenote or Dos Ojos, and snorkeling in the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef. Secrets Playa Mujeres guests can play on-site golf, take a short ferry to Isla Mujeres for snorkeling and village exploring, visit Cancun's underwater sculpture museum, or access Holbox island for whale shark tours in season."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-sunscape-coco-punta-cana":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only luxury all-inclusive on Mexico's quieter Punta Sam coast, north of Cancun, with a heated pool, spa, golf course, tennis, swim-up bar, gym, nightclub, and multiple restaurants requiring no reservations. Sunscape Coco Punta Cana is a budget-friendly family all-inclusive in the Dominican Republic's Punta Cana area with a kids club and teen club but a notably thin amenity offering beyond that. The rating gaps are stark: Secrets leads on food (8.0 vs 6.2), pool (8.0 vs 6.2), atmosphere (8.0 vs 6.2), and room quality (9.0 vs 7.9), while both score similarly on location and cleanliness. Secrets costs more but delivers measurably better across nearly every category. If you want a high-rated adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with a full amenity suite, spa, and golf at a premium price, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres. If you want a budget-friendly Dominican Republic family all-inclusive with kids and teen programming at a lower price point, go to Sunscape Coco Punta Cana.","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples and adult travelers who want a premium, well-appointed Mexican all-inclusive with a spa, golf course, heated pool, swim-up bar, and strong service scores, and are willing to pay top-tier prices for a measurably superior experience away from the Cancun crowds.","whoShouldChooseB":"Budget-conscious families with children and teenagers who want a straightforward Dominican Republic all-inclusive with dedicated kids and teen clubs at a lower price point, and are comfortable with more limited dining and amenity options than a premium resort would offer.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak in winter and spring when northern travelers escape the cold. Mexico's Punta Sam area and Punta Cana share similar Caribbean weather patterns, with the driest, most reliable conditions running November through April. Both carry hurricane risk July through October, with September being the most active month to avoid at either property.","activities":"At Secrets Playa Mujeres, guests can play golf, use the spa, swim laps in the heated pool, play tennis, and access evening entertainment and the nightclub on-site. Sunscape Coco Punta Cana's activity offering is leaner, but Punta Cana's wider resort corridor provides easy access to dune buggy tours, zip-lining, catamaran excursions, and deep-sea fishing for families looking to supplement on-property programming."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-curacao-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is a large adults-only Mexican all-inclusive on the Punta Sam coast north of Cancún, with a golf course, spa, nightclub, swim-up bar, tennis, heated pool, and evening entertainment, scoring an impressive 8.8 overall with standout marks for cleanliness (9.3), service (9.2), and rooms (9.0). Zoëtry Curaçao Resort & Spa is a boutique adults-only property near Willemstad with a strong food score (8.1) and excellent rooms (8.8), but its beach rating is a significant liability at just 3.3 versus Secrets' 7.5, and its pool scores 6.9 against Secrets' 8.0. Zoëtry's overall rating of 7.6 trails Secrets by a full 1.2 points, and its value score of 7.4 versus 8.6 raises questions at the same price tier. Secrets wins on nearly every measurable dimension; Zoëtry's differentiator is Curaçao's distinctive Dutch-Caribbean culture and Willemstad's UNESCO-listed architecture nearby. If beach, pool, and broad amenities matter, Secrets is the clear choice.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or solo travelers who want a polished, amenity-rich Mexican all-inclusive with a golf course, nightclub, and high service standards on a decent beach north of Cancún, and who want strong value for a luxury price point.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults-only couples drawn to Curaçao's unique Dutch-Caribbean culture and UNESCO-listed Willemstad who prioritize intimate boutique atmosphere and quality rooms over beach quality, pool size, or a broad amenity offering, and for whom a destination's distinctiveness outweighs conventional resort metrics.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Playa Mujeres is best visited November through April, avoiding Mexico's hurricane season and summer heat. Curaçao sits outside the main hurricane belt and enjoys consistent trade winds year-round, making Zoëtry a viable option any month, though January through April offers the driest and coolest conditions for both destinations.","activities":"Secrets guests can golf on-site, play tennis, snorkel off the beach, and explore Isla Mujeres by ferry nearby. Zoëtry guests are steps from Willemstad's colorful Handelskade waterfront, world-class scuba diving on Curaçao's protected reefs, and the island's rugged Christoffelpark. Both resorts offer spa treatments, but only Secrets provides the critical mass of on-property diversions for guests who prefer staying within the resort grounds."},"dreams-puerto-morelos-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Puerto Morelos is a family all-inclusive on the Caribbean coast near Puerto Morelos, built around two waterparks, a kids club, and a beach, with strong room (8.5), cleanliness (8.6), and service (8.5) scores but notably weaker food (7.0), pool (6.7), and beach (5.0) ratings. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only all-inclusive near Punta Sam with a golf course, spa, heated pool, swim-up bar, and nightclub, and it outscores Dreams across nearly every category: overall 8.8 vs 7.8, food 8.0 vs 7.0, beach 7.5 vs 5.0, pool 8.0 vs 6.7, room 9.0 vs 8.5, cleanliness 9.3 vs 8.6, and service 9.2 vs 8.5. The beach gap of 2.5 points is particularly striking. Dreams trades on its waterpark infrastructure and family programming; Secrets trades on polish, a golf course, and a consistently higher-rated guest experience across the board. Both sit at the same price tier, making Secrets the stronger value proposition for adults at 8.6 vs Dreams' 7.8.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children who want a Mexican Caribbean all-inclusive anchored by two waterparks and a kids club. The strong room, cleanliness, and service scores mean parents will be comfortable, even if the beach and pool ratings suggest managing expectations on those fronts.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want a highly polished, adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with a golf course, spa, heated pool, and nightclub. Secrets Playa Mujeres consistently outrates Dreams across food, beach, pool, atmosphere, and service, making it the clear choice for guests traveling without children.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is lowest and humidity manageable. July and August are popular for families at Dreams given school holidays, though hurricane season runs June through November. Secrets sees strong demand during winter months and holiday periods; shoulder seasons like May or early November offer quieter conditions at both properties.","activities":"Dreams guests can use both waterparks, access the beach, and explore Puerto Morelos town nearby, including its coral reef protected as a national marine park and good local diving and snorkelling. Secrets guests can play the on-site golf course, use the spa and tennis courts, enjoy the swim-up bar and nightclub, or take day trips to Isla Mujeres, just offshore, for beaches, golf carts, and snorkelling."},"dreams-playa-bonita-panama-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Playa Bonita Panama is a family-oriented all-inclusive near Panama City with solid service (8.1) and cleanliness (8.0) ratings, but its beach score of 4.0 is a significant weakness, and food (6.7), pool (6.6), and atmosphere (6.5) all sit in mediocre territory. Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only all-inclusive north of Cancún that outperforms Dreams across every single rated category: overall 8.8 vs 7.4, food 8.0 vs 6.7, beach 7.5 vs 4.0, rooms 9.0 vs 7.6, and cleanliness 9.3 vs 8.0. Secrets also carries a far more comprehensive amenity set — heated pool, golf course, spa, gym, nightclub, swim-up bar, and tennis — while Dreams offers little beyond a kids club. The core trade-off is geography and guest profile: Dreams is a family resort in an unusual, non-beach Caribbean destination, while Secrets is a polished adults-only retreat on a genuine beach near Cancún with consistently superior ratings across the board.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families visiting Panama City who want a convenient all-inclusive base with young children welcome, strong service scores, and easy access to one of Central America's most compelling urban and wildlife destinations, and who can accept a weak beach situation.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want a high-performing Mexican all-inclusive with a genuine beach, excellent rooms (9.0), a golf course, spa, and nightclub, and who prioritize consistent quality — cleanliness 9.3, service 9.2 — over novelty of destination.","whenToVisit":"Panama City is warm year-round; the dry season runs December through April, making those months best for Dreams Playa Bonita. Secrets Playa Mujeres benefits from Mexico's Yucatán dry season, also December through April, when humidity drops and hurricane risk is minimal. Both resorts are busiest over Christmas and Easter; shoulder months of May and November offer lower rates at Secrets with only marginally higher rain risk.","activities":"Dreams guests can explore Panama City's UNESCO-listed Casco Viejo, the Panama Canal, and nearby rainforest and wildlife reserves — the resort's location score of 7.6 reflects genuine off-property appeal. Secrets guests have the Caribbean Sea, a golf course on-site, tennis, spa, and watersports, plus proximity to Isla Mujeres, Cancún's lagoon, and cenote day trips into the Yucatán interior."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-sunscape-puerto-vallarta-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only luxury all-inclusive on a quieter stretch north of Cancun in Punta Sam, with a golf course, heated pool, spa, swim-up bar, and strong across-the-board ratings: cleanliness 9.3, service 9.2, rooms 9.0, and an overall score of 8.8. Sunscape Puerto Vallarta Resort & Spa is a family-friendly mid-market all-inclusive on Banderas Bay in Puerto Vallarta with a notably lower overall score of 8.0 and significant gaps in food (6.2 vs 8.0), beach (5.3 vs 7.5), pool (6.0 vs 8.0), and atmosphere (6.2 vs 8.0). Secrets commands a higher price point but delivers measurably better rooms, service, and cleanliness in a secluded adults-only setting with golf. Sunscape offers a more accessible price in one of Mexico's most characterful resort towns, but its ratings suggest a resort that underdelivers on core all-inclusive fundamentals. If you want polished adults-only luxury near Cancun with golf, go Secrets. If you want a budget-friendly family base in Puerto Vallarta, go Sunscape.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples and solo travelers who want a high-end, secluded Mexican all-inclusive near Cancun with exceptional service, pristine rooms, a golf course, and a spa-forward atmosphere well away from the crowded Hotel Zone.","whoShouldChooseB":"Budget-conscious families who prioritize Puerto Vallarta's lively town, cobblestone streets, and Pacific coast culture over resort-level food and beach quality, and who are happy to use the resort primarily as a comfortable, well-located base.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's dry season between December and April. Secrets Playa Mujeres sits in the Caribbean hurricane corridor, making June through October riskier. Puerto Vallarta's rainy season runs June through October as well, though storms are typically shorter-lived than Caribbean systems. High season for both runs late November through Easter, with the best combination of weather and value found in February and March.","activities":"Secrets guests can play the on-site golf course, use the heated pool, take spa treatments, and access watersports along the calm Punta Sam coastline, with day trips to Isla Mujeres and Cancun nearby. Sunscape guests in Puerto Vallarta can explore the Malecon boardwalk, the Zona Romantica, and Los Muertos Beach, plus arrange whale-watching tours from December to March, zip-lining in the Sierra Madre foothills, and sport fishing on Banderas Bay."},"dreams-cozumel-cape-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Cozumel Cape Resort & Spa is a family-friendly Mexican all-inclusive on Cozumel island, rated 7.3 overall, with strong room (8.2), cleanliness (8.5), and service (8.3) scores but a notably weak beach rating of 5.3 and food rating of 6.8. Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only resort on Mexico's mainland near Punta Sam, rated 8.8 overall, with significantly higher scores across nearly every category: food (8.0 vs 6.8), beach (7.5 vs 5.3), pool (8.0 vs 6.7), cleanliness (9.3 vs 8.5), service (9.2 vs 8.3), and sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.3). Secrets also offers a fuller amenity set including a golf course, heated pool, spa, gym, tennis, nightclub, and swim-up bar. The core trade-off is family access and an island setting at Dreams versus a substantially higher-rated, amenity-rich adults-only experience at Secrets. If you are traveling with children and want Cozumel's diving and island atmosphere, Dreams makes sense. If you want a polished, high-performing adults-only resort with golf and consistent quality near Cancun, Secrets is the clear choice.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children, including toddlers under 4, who want a Cozumel island base for diving and snorkeling excursions and can accept a weaker beach and food offering in exchange for an island setting and strong room quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or adult groups who want a high-performing, adults-only Mexican resort with golf, a spa, heated pool, nightclub, and consistently excellent service and cleanliness scores, without the distractions of a family property.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's dry season between December and April, when weather is most reliable and humidity lowest. Cozumel's diving is exceptional year-round but peaks in the dry season. Playa Mujeres is close to Cancun and shares the same seasonal patterns. Both sit within the Caribbean hurricane belt, so July through October carries elevated weather risk.","activities":"Dreams Cozumel's greatest draw is off-property: Cozumel is one of the world's premier scuba diving and snorkeling destinations, with nearby reefs and cenotes accessible by short boat trip. Secrets Playa Mujeres keeps guests on-site with its 18-hole golf course, spa, tennis courts, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment, while the Isla Mujeres ferry and Cancun attractions are a short drive away."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-sunscape-sabor-cozumel":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only luxury all-inclusive on the Punta Sam peninsula north of Cancun, with a golf course, spa, heated pool, swim-up bar, nightclub, tennis, and evening entertainment, earning an overall rating of 8.8 against Sunscape Sabor Cozumel's 7.6. The rating gaps are significant and consistent: food scores 8.0 vs 6.1, beach 7.5 vs 5.8, pool 8.0 vs 5.8, atmosphere 8.0 vs 6.2, and rooms 9.0 vs 7.2. Sunscape Sabor is a budget-friendly family all-inclusive on Cozumel island with a beach and little else listed in amenities, at half the price point. Secrets earns its premium through strong cleanliness (9.3), service (9.2), and sleep quality (9.1) scores. Sunscape's strongest suits are service (8.2) and cleanliness (8.0), respectable for its price tier. If you want a polished adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with golf, spa, and full amenity coverage near Cancun, choose Secrets. If you want an affordable family beach base on Cozumel near world-class diving reefs, choose Sunscape.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples and solo travelers who want a high-end, amenity-rich Mexican all-inclusive with a golf course, spa, heated pool, and nightclub near Cancun, and are willing to pay a premium for strong service scores (9.2) and well-appointed rooms (9.0).","whoShouldChooseB":"Budget-conscious families who want a simple, affordable all-inclusive base on Cozumel island, prioritizing access to the island's legendary coral reefs and dive sites over resort amenities, and who are comfortable with more modest food and pool ratings.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's Caribbean dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is lowest and winds are calm. Cozumel's diving visibility peaks in the dry season. Avoid hurricane season, June through November, at both properties, though Cozumel's island position can make weather more unpredictable than the Cancun-area mainland location of Secrets Playa Mujeres.","activities":"Secrets Playa Mujeres guests can play the on-site golf course, use the spa and tennis courts, and take day trips to Isla Mujeres or Cancun. Sunscape Sabor Cozumel guests are steps from some of the world's best scuba diving and snorkeling along the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef, with dive shops, reef tours, and the town of San Miguel offering local restaurants and ferry connections to the Yucatan mainland."},"dreams-acapulco-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Acapulco Resort & Spa is a family-oriented Mexican all-inclusive on the Pacific coast in Acapulco, with a kids club for under-4s and no-reservation dining, carrying modest ratings across most categories: food at 6.5, beach at 6.0, pool at 6.2, and overall at 7.4. Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only, premium all-inclusive in Punta Sam near Cancún on the Caribbean coast, with a golf course, heated pool, spa, swim-up bar, nightclub, and tennis, scoring significantly higher across every category: overall 8.8, food 8.0, beach 7.5, pool 8.0, room 9.0, cleanliness 9.3, and service 9.2. The gap in room quality alone — 7.4 versus 9.0 — reflects a fundamentally different tier of product. Dreams Acapulco suits budget-conscious families on the Pacific side; Secrets Playa Mujeres is a high-end adults-only Caribbean resort where the premium price point is clearly justified by the ratings.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children, including toddlers, who want a no-frills Pacific Mexico all-inclusive in Acapulco at a lower price point, and are comfortable with below-average food and beach scores in exchange for accessible pricing and easy no-reservation dining.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who want a premium adults-only Caribbean all-inclusive near Cancún with exceptional rooms, cleanliness, and service, plus a golf course, spa, heated pool, and nightclub, and are willing to pay top-tier prices for a resort that consistently delivers on every metric.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Playa Mujeres sits in the Caribbean hurricane belt; avoid late August through October and target November through April for the best conditions. Dreams Acapulco on the Pacific coast sees a rainy season from June through October, with the dry season from November to May being the most reliable. Both resorts offer better value and availability in shoulder months like May or November outside of Mexican holiday weeks.","activities":"At Secrets Playa Mujeres, guests can play golf on the on-site course, use the spa, swim in the heated pool, visit the swim-up bar, play tennis, and enjoy evening entertainment and nightclub access, all within a short drive of Isla Mujeres ferry and Cancún. At Dreams Acapulco, the surrounding bay offers parasailing, sport fishing, and cliff-diving spectacles at La Quebrada, with the resort itself providing a more limited activity roster centered on the beach and pool area."},"secrets-aura-cozumel-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Aura Cozumel and Secrets Playa Mujeres are both adults-only Mexican all-inclusives at the same price tier, but their ratings tell a starkly different story. Playa Mujeres outscores Aura Cozumel across every single category: overall 8.8 vs 7.4, rooms 9.0 vs 7.6, cleanliness 9.3 vs 8.1, service 9.2 vs 8.3, and value 8.6 vs 7.2. The beach gap is notable — 7.5 vs 5.5 — and Playa Mujeres adds amenities Cozumel lacks entirely: a golf course, heated pool, spa, gym, tennis, swim-up bar, nightclub, and evening entertainment. Cozumel's advantages are narrower: a strong location score of 8.3 and direct access to the world-class Mesoamerican Reef for diving and snorkelling, which is the island's primary draw. If you are not specifically coming for Cozumel's underwater world, the numbers make Playa Mujeres the objectively stronger resort in nearly every measurable dimension.","whoShouldChooseA":"Divers, snorkellers, and ocean enthusiasts who want to be on Cozumel specifically for the Mesoamerican Reef — one of the world's top dive sites. Couples who prioritise an island setting and easy access to Cozumel's town, reefs, and ferry connections over resort amenities and polish.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults and couples who want a comprehensively appointed resort with a spa, golf, heated pool, swim-up bar, and nightclub, and who value cleanliness, service, and room quality above all. Playa Mujeres suits those who want to stay on-property and feel genuinely pampered rather than using the resort as a base for outside excursions.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's Caribbean dry season, roughly December through April, with lower humidity and reduced storm risk. Cozumel's diving is exceptional year-round but visibility peaks November through May. Playa Mujeres, near Cancun, shares the same seasonal pattern. Avoid late August through October when hurricane activity peaks across the Yucatan Peninsula.","activities":"Cozumel is defined by its proximity to the Mesoamerican Reef — diving, snorkelling, and glass-bottom boat tours dominate. The island's town offers cycling, local restaurants, and ferry trips to Playa del Carmen. Playa Mujeres keeps guests on-property with golf, tennis, a spa, and a swim-up bar, while nearby Isla Mujeres is reachable by ferry, and Cancun's Zona Hotelera and cenotes are accessible day-trip options."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-sunscape-curacao-resort-spa-and-casino":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only luxury all-inclusive on Mexico's Isla Mujeres coast with an 18-hole golf course, heated pool, spa, swim-up bar, nightclub, and tennis, earning standout scores in cleanliness (9.3), service (9.2), rooms (9.0), and an overall 8.8. Sunscape Curacao is a family all-inclusive near Willemstad with a spa and casino, but trails significantly across almost every rating category: overall 7.3, food 6.2, pool 6.0, beach 6.3, and atmosphere 6.2, with location (8.1) its strongest suit. The gap between these two properties is substantial. Secrets outperforms Sunscape by 1.5 points overall, 1.8 points on food, and 1.5 points on beach quality. Secrets is a polished, amenity-rich adults retreat in Mexico; Sunscape is a family option in a genuinely interesting Caribbean destination that compensates for weaker resort ratings with Willemstad's colonial architecture and culture nearby. At the same price tier, Secrets delivers considerably more resort quality for the dollar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or solo travelers who want a high-performing, amenity-packed Mexican all-inclusive with outstanding service, immaculate rooms, a championship golf course, and a spa, and who prioritize on-resort quality over exploring a local destination.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families drawn to Curaçao's distinctive Dutch-Caribbean culture and Willemstad's UNESCO-listed waterfront who are willing to accept a more modest resort experience in exchange for a genuinely unique island destination that stands apart from typical Caribbean all-inclusive settings.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Playa Mujeres is best visited November through April during Mexico's dry season, avoiding peak hurricane risk. Sunscape Curacao benefits from the island's position outside the hurricane belt, making it a reliable year-round destination, though December through April offers the driest, most comfortable conditions. Both resorts carry premium pricing during the North American winter holiday period.","activities":"At Secrets Playa Mujeres, guests can play golf on the on-site 18-hole course, use the spa and tennis courts, and take day trips to Isla Mujeres or Cancun's cenotes and Mayan ruins. At Sunscape Curacao, the UNESCO-listed Willemstad is a short drive away, with options for diving the island's renowned reefs, exploring Christoffel National Park, and visiting the Hato Caves alongside the resort's casino and spa."},"dreams-curacao-resort-spa-and-casino-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Curaçao Resort, Spa & Casino is a family-friendly all-inclusive on the Dutch Caribbean island of Curaçao near Willemstad, with a casino, kids club for under-4s, and a location that scores well at 7.9, but its overall rating of 6.4 trails Secrets Playa Mujeres significantly. Beach scores particularly low at 5.3, and value sits at just 6.4 despite a $$$$price tag. Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only Mexican all-inclusive in Punta Sam with golf, heated pool, spa, swim-up bar, and nightclub, earning an outstanding overall rating of 8.8. It outperforms Dreams Curaçao across every single rated category — cleanliness (9.3 vs 7.8), service (9.2 vs 7.3), rooms (9.0 vs 7.3), value (8.6 vs 6.4), and beach (7.5 vs 5.3). Dreams Curaçao offers a family setting with Caribbean island character and city proximity; Secrets Playa Mujeres delivers a polished, adults-only luxury experience at considerably better value for money.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children who want to explore the Dutch Caribbean from a Willemstad-adjacent base and can accept a resort that scores modestly across most categories. Best suited to those prioritising island culture and proximity to Curaçao's historic city centre over beach quality or resort polish.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travellers seeking a high-performing, adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with golf, spa, swim-up bar, and nightclub. With a 9.2 service rating and 9.3 for cleanliness, Secrets Playa Mujeres is ideal for those who want a genuinely luxurious, well-executed all-inclusive experience at a price that justifies the spend.","whenToVisit":"Curaçao sits outside the hurricane belt, making Dreams Curaçao viable year-round with dry, sunny conditions from January through September being the sweet spot. Secrets Playa Mujeres near Cancún is best visited November through April, when humidity drops and hurricane risk is minimal. Both resorts carry a $$$$ price level, with peak season pricing in Mexico running December through March.","activities":"Dreams Curaçao guests can explore Willemstad's UNESCO-listed colonial architecture, snorkel Curaçao's renowned coral reefs, and try their luck at the on-site casino. Secrets Playa Mujeres guests can play the on-site golf course, use the heated pool and swim-up bar, book spa treatments, and access the nearby Isla Mujeres by ferry for snorkelling, diving, and exploring a small Caribbean island town."},"breathless-puerto-vallarta-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Puerto Vallarta and Secrets Playa Mujeres are both adults-only Mexican all-inclusives at the same price tier, but they diverge meaningfully in setting, amenities, and guest experience. Breathless sits in Puerto Vallarta with a standout location score of 8.7 and exceptional room ratings (9.1), benefiting from the city's culture and nightlife nearby. Secrets Playa Mujeres, on a quieter stretch north of Cancún near Isla Mujeres, scores higher on beach (7.5 vs. 6.5), pool (8 vs. 7), atmosphere (8 vs. 7.5), food (8 vs. 7.7), and sleep quality (9.1 vs. 8.5), and adds a full golf course and heated pool that Breathless lacks. Both score identically on cleanliness (9.3) and service (9.2). Secrets edges out Breathless on overall polish and amenity breadth, while Breathless wins on room quality and proximity to a vibrant urban destination. If you want livelier surroundings and a stronger room, go to Breathless Puerto Vallarta. If you want a more serene, amenity-rich resort with golf, a better beach, and superior sleep scores, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want an urban-adjacent Mexican all-inclusive with excellent rooms and easy access to Puerto Vallarta's restaurants, culture, and nightlife. Best for couples or solo travelers who value location and a lively atmosphere over a resort-centric experience.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults seeking a well-rounded, quieter all-inclusive with a golf course, heated pool, superior beach, and strong food scores in a secluded Yucatán setting. Ideal for couples who want to stay on property and unwind rather than explore a nearby city.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Mexico's dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is minimal and temperatures are comfortable. Puerto Vallarta's peak season runs November to April, avoiding the summer rainy season. Playa Mujeres near Cancún shares a similar pattern but is also susceptible to Atlantic hurricane season from June through November, so late spring or winter visits are advisable for both.","activities":"Breathless Puerto Vallarta guests can explore the Malecón boardwalk, old town restaurants, whale watching seasonally, and zip-lining in the Sierra Madre foothills nearby. Secrets Playa Mujeres offers on-site golf, tennis, and watersports, with ferry access to Isla Mujeres for snorkeling, cenote diving, and exploring the island's charming town. Both properties offer spa services, swim-up bars, and evening entertainment on site."},"dreams-grand-island-cancun-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Grand Island Cancun is a family-focused all-inclusive in Costa Mujeres with a kids club for under-4s and standout service (9.1) and cleanliness (9.0), but its food (7.2), beach (6.1), pool (7.1), and atmosphere (6.9) ratings all trail Secrets Playa Mujeres by a meaningful margin. Secrets Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is an adults-only property in Punta Sam with a golf course, heated pool, spa, nightclub, and tennis, posting stronger scores across food (8.0), beach (7.5), pool (8.0), atmosphere (8.0), room (9.0), and value (8.6). Both share the same $$$ price tier and no-reservation dining policy, but Secrets delivers a noticeably more polished all-around experience for couples and adult travelers. If you want a clean, well-serviced family resort near Cancun with a toddler-friendly kids club and excellent sleep quality, go to Dreams Grand Island. If you want an adults-only Golf & Spa resort with superior food, beach, and amenity ratings in a quieter coastal setting, go to Secrets Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children, including toddlers and infants, who prioritize cleanliness, attentive service, and a relaxed environment over nightlife and dining variety. The strong sleep quality score (9.0) and kids club for under-4s make it particularly well-suited to parents traveling with babies.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who want a fully equipped adults-only resort with golf, spa, heated pool, nightclub, and a beach that outrates most Cancun-area properties. Those who place a premium on food quality, room comfort (9.0), and overall value (8.6) will find Secrets the stronger all-round package.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in the greater Cancun corridor and share the same seasonal logic. December through April delivers dry, sunny weather and peak pricing. May and June offer lower rates with manageable heat before hurricane season intensifies July through October. November is a strong shoulder-season option, with quieter crowds, lower prices, and weather that is generally still reliable.","activities":"Both resorts are within reach of Isla Mujeres ferry terminals, making a day trip to the island a natural excursion. Secrets adds on-site golf, tennis, and a full spa. The wider Cancun area offers snorkeling at Isla Contoy, swimming with whale sharks seasonally, cenote tours, and Chichen Itza day trips. Dreams guests with families will find water park access and kid-oriented excursions readily available through local operators."},"secrets-macao-beach-punta-cana-vs-secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Both are adults-only Secrets properties at the same price tier with identical cleanliness (9.3), service (9.2), and sleep quality (9.1) scores, but they diverge meaningfully on beach and location. Secrets Macao Beach Punta Cana posts a notably stronger beach rating (8.2 vs 7.5) and a higher location score (9.0 vs 8.9), anchored on one of the Dominican Republic's most acclaimed natural beaches. Secrets Playa Mujeres edges ahead on overall score (8.8 vs 8.5) and value (8.6 vs 8.4), and adds a full golf course, heated pool, spa, and tennis to its amenity list, making it a more activity-rich resort. Macao Beach wins on raw beach quality and room ratings (9.1 vs 9.0), while Playa Mujeres compensates with a broader on-site amenity package in a quieter Cancun-adjacent location north of the hotel zone. Food scores are close but both sit in the low 8s, so neither should be chosen primarily for dining. The choice comes down to beach versus amenities.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults and couples who prioritize an exceptional natural beach experience above all else. Macao Beach is widely regarded as one of the Dominican Republic's finest stretches of sand, and its room and location scores reflect a resort built around that setting. Best for those who want sun, sand, and seclusion over on-site activity variety.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults and couples who want a fuller activity roster alongside their beach holiday. The addition of golf, tennis, a heated pool, and a dedicated spa makes Playa Mujeres the stronger pick for those who want structured options beyond the beach, and its slightly better overall and value scores reward guests who will use what the resort offers.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak in winter and spring. For Punta Cana, December through April delivers dry, stable weather with low humidity. Playa Mujeres, just north of Cancun, follows a similar pattern, with January through May offering the most reliable conditions. Both regions sit in the Atlantic hurricane corridor, so August through October carries the highest weather risk regardless of which resort you choose.","activities":"At Secrets Macao Beach, the headline activity is the beach itself, one of the Dominican Republic's most photographed natural bays, with watersports readily accessible nearby. Secrets Playa Mujeres offers golf on-site, tennis, a spa, and swim-up bar, with Isla Mujeres a short ferry ride away for snorkelling, cycling, and exploring. Cancun's broader dining, nightlife, and excursion network, including Chichen Itza and Coba, is also within reach from Playa Mujeres."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-huatulco-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, with a waterpark for kids and big kids, lazy river, kids club for under-4s, teen club, babysitting, adult pool, and rooms accommodating 5 or more guests. Secrets Huatulco Resort & Spa is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific Oaxacan coast in Huatulco, with snorkelling, a nightclub, room service, and a notably higher atmosphere rating (7.9 vs 7.4) and location rating (9.1 vs 8.6). Dreams Onyx scores higher overall (9.1 vs 8.8) and on service is essentially tied, while Secrets Huatulco edges it on food (7.9 vs 7.6), beach (6.8 vs 6.5), room quality (8.9 vs 8.7), and atmosphere. The core split is family infrastructure versus an adults-only Pacific Mexico escape. If you want a Dominican Republic family all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, kids clubs across all age groups, and large-group rooms, go to Dreams Onyx. If you want a quieter, adults-only Mexican all-inclusive on the less-trafficked Huatulco coast with a nightclub, snorkelling, and a stronger sense of atmosphere, go to Secrets Huatulco.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages, including toddlers, who want a Dominican Republic all-inclusive packed with kid-focused infrastructure — waterparks, lazy river, dedicated clubs by age group, babysitting — alongside adult amenities and rooms that sleep five or more.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who want a peaceful, adults-only Pacific Mexico escape on the understated Huatulco coastline, with snorkelling, a nightclub, room service, and an atmosphere that consistently outscores the typical Caribbean family resort.","whenToVisit":"Punta Cana is a year-round destination with peak season running December through April when rainfall is lowest. Huatulco on Mexico's Pacific coast is best visited November through May, its dry season, with the shoulder months of November and May offering good value. Both resorts sit in the same price tier, so timing decisions hinge more on weather than cost.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx guests can use the waterparks, lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, and evening entertainment within the resort, with Punta Cana excursions including dune buggies, catamaran trips, and cenote visits nearby. At Secrets Huatulco, snorkelling directly from the resort and evening entertainment are complemented by the broader Huatulco national park — home to 36 bays — with boat tours, sport fishing, zip-lining, and coffee plantation visits all accessible locally."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-bahia-mita-surf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, with a waterpark for little and big kids, a lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and rooms accommodating five or more guests. Secrets Bahia Mita Surf & Spa Resort is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Riviera Nayarit coast near Punta de Mita, with a heated pool, nightclub, pet-friendly policy, and a quieter, more intimate atmosphere. The ratings reveal meaningful contrasts: Secrets edges out Dreams on rooms (9.1 vs 8.7), cleanliness (9.3 vs 9.1), service (9.2 vs 9.0), and atmosphere (7.7 vs 7.4), while Dreams leads significantly on beach (6.5 vs 5.0) and overall score (9.1 vs 8.9). Dreams is the clear choice for families needing dedicated children's infrastructure, while Secrets offers a more polished, adult-focused retreat on Mexico's Pacific coast. Food ratings are close, with Secrets holding a slight edge (7.8 vs 7.6).","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a comprehensive Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and large-group rooms, all backed by strong cleanliness and service scores in Punta Cana.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples and solo travelers who want a refined, adults-only Pacific Mexico all-inclusive near Punta de Mita with top-tier rooms, excellent service, a nightclub, heated pool, and the option to bring their pet.","whenToVisit":"Punta Cana's dry season runs December through April, making those months ideal for Dreams Onyx. Punta de Mita on Mexico's Riviera Nayarit enjoys its driest, calmest weather from November through May, with humpback whale season from December through March adding a notable natural draw near Secrets Bahia Mita.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can enjoy Punta Cana's watersports, catamaran excursions, and nearby golf courses, plus on-site waterparks and evening entertainment. Secrets Bahia Mita sits near world-class surf breaks at Sayulita and La Lancha, whale-watching tours, sport fishing, and the Islas Marietas National Park, a protected marine reserve with snorkeling and a famous hidden beach."},"dreams-huatulco-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Huatulco and Dreams Onyx are both four-dollar-sign family all-inclusives in the Dreams brand, but they sit in meaningfully different destinations and diverge on key amenity sets. Huatulco is on Mexico's Pacific coast in Tangolunda Bay, earning a standout location score of 8.9 versus Onyx's 8.6, and it leads on beach score 7.3 to 6.5, making it the stronger pick for guests whose holiday revolves around the ocean. Onyx counters with a notably better pool setup, scoring 7.4 against Huatulco's 6.9, and backs that up with a waterpark for both little and big kids, a lazy river, and a swim-up bar that Huatulco simply doesn't have. Onyx also scores higher overall at 9.1 versus 8.9 and edges out Huatulco on sleep quality 9.1 to 8.7. Huatulco adds watersports depth with snorkelling, windsurfing, fishing, and archery that Onyx doesn't list, while Onyx covers families with older children better through its dedicated teen club and rooms accommodating five or more guests.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and couples drawn to Mexico's quieter Pacific coast who want a well-located, activity-rich resort with snorkelling, windsurfing, fishing, and archery on a better-rated beach. Those who prefer a more relaxed, less infrastructure-heavy setting over a Dominican mega-resort will find Huatulco the stronger fit.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with a range of ages, including teenagers and groups of five or more, who want a Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, and swim-up bar at a slightly higher overall rating. Guests who prioritise pool-centred holidays over beach quality will get more from Onyx's water amenities lineup.","whenToVisit":"Huatulco on Mexico's Pacific coast is driest and calmest from November through April, with the rainy season running June through October. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana benefits from the Dominican Republic's year-round warmth, with the driest months falling December through April. Both resorts sit outside peak hurricane zones relative to other Caribbean destinations, though Punta Cana carries more hurricane-season risk from August through October.","activities":"At Huatulco, guests can snorkel, windsurf, fish, practice archery, join yoga classes, and explore Tangolunda Bay's protected coves and nearby national park. At Onyx in Punta Cana, on-site waterparks, a lazy river, and a swim-up bar anchor the days, with Punta Cana's zip-lining, dune buggy tours, deep-sea fishing, and the Indigenous Eyes Ecological Reserve all accessible as excursions from the resort."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-playa-esmeralda-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana rated an impressive 9.1 overall, with standout scores for cleanliness (9.1), sleep quality (9.1), and service (9.0), and a sprawling amenity set that includes a waterpark, lazy river, kids club for under-4s, teen club, adult pool, babysitting, and rooms that sleep five or more. Its beach rating is notably low at 6.5 and food scores a modest 7.6. Secrets Playa Esmeralda is an adults-only retreat in the quieter Miches area rated 8.2 overall, with a meaningfully better beach score of 8.5 and solid food at 8.0, but a thinner amenity list that covers only the basics. It sits at a lower price tier despite its more secluded, boutique-leaning setting. Dreams Onyx wins on overall satisfaction and family infrastructure; Secrets Playa Esmeralda wins on beach quality and a more tranquil, couples-oriented atmosphere. If you want a high-rated Dominican family mega-resort with waterslides and extensive kids programming, choose Dreams Onyx. If you want an adults-only escape on a genuinely good beach in the less-crowded Miches region at a lower price, choose Secrets Playa Esmeralda.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a premium, highly rated Punta Cana all-inclusive packed with kids clubs, waterparks, a lazy river, babysitting, and large-group rooms, and who prioritize service and cleanliness over beach quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or friends who want a quieter, beach-forward Dominican escape away from the Punta Cana resort corridor, with a solid beach score of 8.5, good food, and a more relaxed adults-only atmosphere at a lower price point.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from the Dominican Republic's dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is minimal and humidity is lower. Miches, where Secrets Playa Esmeralda sits, is notably more lush and can see more rainfall than Punta Cana year-round, so the dry season advantage matters even more there. Both properties are busiest over Christmas, New Year, and spring break, when rates and crowds peak.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can enjoy on-site waterparks, a lazy river, swim-up bars, evening entertainment, and spa treatments, with Punta Cana's busy strip of excursions, zip-lining, cenote tours, and Saona Island day trips nearby. Secrets Playa Esmeralda guests benefit from Miches's proximity to Los Haitises National Park, mangrove boat tours, and horseback riding on the beach, offering a more nature-oriented excursion menu alongside on-site spa and gym facilities."},"breathless-punta-cana-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Both resorts sit in Punta Cana at the same $$$$ price level with identical food (7.6), beach (6.5), pool (7.4), and atmosphere (7.4) ratings, so the real dividing line is guest type and amenities. Breathless is adults-only, built around a nightclub, casino, snorkelling, diving, and tennis, with a strong service score (8.9) and a lively, social atmosphere. Dreams Onyx is a family all-inclusive that edges ahead on almost every comfort metric: overall 9.1 vs 8.8, cleanliness 9.1 vs 9.0, sleep quality 9.1 vs 8.3, value 8.7 vs 8.4, and service 9.0 vs 8.9. Dreams adds a kids club for under-4s, a teen club, babysitting, two waterparks, rooms that sleep 5+, and reservation-free dining. Breathless counters with a casino, nightclub, diving, and the exclusivity of an adults-only environment. The sleep quality gap of 0.8 points likely reflects the noise differential between a nightclub-equipped adults resort and a family property designed for restful stays.","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples or groups of adults who want an energetic Punta Cana all-inclusive with a nightclub, casino, diving, and a social atmosphere, and who are happy to trade a slightly lower sleep quality and value score for an exclusively adult environment.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of any age who want a polished, high-scoring Punta Cana all-inclusive with two waterparks, a kids club from infancy, a teen club, babysitting, reservation-free dining, and rooms large enough for five or more guests.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Punta Cana's dry season, December through April, when rainfall is lowest and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Peak weeks around Christmas and spring break push prices up and occupancy high at both properties. May through November brings lower rates and occasional tropical weather; hurricane season peaks September through October and is worth monitoring.","activities":"Both resorts offer beach access, lazy river, swim-up bar, evening entertainment, buffet, gym, and spa on property. Breathless adds diving, snorkelling, tennis, a casino, and a nightclub. Dreams Onyx covers families with two waterparks and structured kids programming. Off-property, guests at either resort can access Punta Cana's deep-sea fishing, zip-lining, ATV excursions, Saona Island day trips, and the Scape Park adventure complex."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark, lazy river, adult pool, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment on a well-established resort corridor. Dreams Playa Mujeres Golf & Spa Resort is a large Mexican family all-inclusive north of Cancún on a quieter stretch of coast, offering the same core family amenities plus a golf course, mini golf, and a nightclub. The two resorts share the same price tier and many amenities, but differ meaningfully in beach and pool ratings: Playa Mujeres scores 7.5 and 8.0 respectively versus Onyx's 6.5 and 7.4, a notable gap. Playa Mujeres also edges ahead on food (7.9 vs 7.6) and room quality (9.0 vs 8.7). Onyx counters with slightly stronger overall (9.1 vs 8.9) and value scores (8.7 vs 8.4). The defining practical difference is destination: Punta Cana for Onyx, a secluded Mexican coast with golf for Playa Mujeres.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a strong-value Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, adult pool, and a full kids and teen program in the heart of Punta Cana's resort strip, and who prioritize overall satisfaction and value scores over beach and pool quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who want a higher-quality beach and pool experience in a quieter, less crowded Mexican coastal setting, with the added bonus of an on-site golf course, mini golf, and a nightclub for parents after the kids are down.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts enjoy warm Caribbean-adjacent climates year-round. Punta Cana's peak season runs December through April, with hurricane risk highest August through October. Playa Mujeres near Cancún follows a similar pattern, with peak season December through April and hurricane season June through November. Both destinations are most pleasant and least rainy in the winter and early spring months.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, guests enjoy the waterpark, lazy river, adult pool, swim-up bar, beach, and evening entertainment, with Punta Cana's broader resort strip offering golf, dune buggies, and cenote excursions nearby. At Dreams Playa Mujeres, guests have the same water amenities plus an on-site golf course, mini golf, and nightclub, with Isla Mujeres day trips, Cancún excursions, and snorkeling tours easily accessible from the property."},"dreams-dominicus-la-romana-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Both are four-dollar-sign Dreams family all-inclusives in the Dominican Republic, but they diverge on beach quality, water amenities, and overall guest satisfaction. Dreams Dominicus La Romana in Bayahibe scores a notably higher beach rating of 7.8 versus Dreams Onyx's 6.5, a meaningful 1.3-point gap that signals a genuinely better stretch of sand. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana pulls ahead on nearly every service metric: overall 9.1 versus 8.7, cleanliness 9.1 versus 8.9, service 9.0 versus 8.8, and sleep quality 9.1 versus 8.6. Onyx also edges out on food at 7.6 versus 7.2 and adds a lazy river and a waterpark for older kids, while Dominicus counters with diving, snorkelling, watersports rentals, yoga, a nightclub, and a teen club with more active programming. Dominicus wins on beach; Onyx wins on operational polish, sleep quality, and pool infrastructure. The Bayahibe location of Dominicus also provides easier access to natural parks and dive sites unavailable from Punta Cana.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and active travellers who prioritise a superior beach, on-site diving and snorkelling, watersports rentals, and a nightclub, and who are happy to trade a slightly lower service polish for a more naturally beautiful Bayahibe setting with access to nearby marine parks.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who put a premium on immaculate cleanliness, consistently high service scores, restful sleep, and strong pool infrastructure including a lazy river and waterpark for older kids, and who can accept a weaker beach in exchange for a more operationally refined Punta Cana resort experience.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts share the Dominican Republic's peak dry season from December through April, when sunshine is reliable and humidity is lower. Bayahibe and Punta Cana both see higher rainfall from May through November, with September and October carrying the greatest hurricane risk. Shoulder months of May and November offer reduced crowds and lower rates at both properties with generally manageable weather.","activities":"Dreams Dominicus La Romana sits near Saona Island and the underwater parks of the Bayahibe marine reserve, making it the stronger base for diving, snorkelling excursions, and catamaran day trips. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana offers convenient access to the region's ATV tours, zip-lining, and cenote swimming. Both resorts provide evening entertainment, swim-up bars, spas, and kids programming on site."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-vista-cancun-golf-and-spa-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a family all-inclusive in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, with a lazy river, waterparks for both age groups, swim-up bar, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and evening entertainment on a beach that rates a modest 6.5. Dreams Vista Cancun Golf & Spa Resort is a family all-inclusive on the Cancun hotel zone in Mexico, adding a Flowrider, golf course, diving, windsurfing, snorkelling, yoga, arcade, heated pool, nightclub, room service, and pet-friendly policy, but its beach scores a notably weak 4.0 against Onyx's already average 6.5. Both resorts share identical food (7.6), pool (7.4), value (8.7), and service (9.0) ratings, making the real differentiators the water-feature lineup and beach quality. Onyx edges Vista on atmosphere (7.4 vs 7.1) and location (8.6 vs 8.3), while Vista narrowly leads on room score (9.0 vs 8.7) and cleanliness (9.2 vs 9.1). If you want a Dominican Republic family all-inclusive with a lazy river, bigger waterpark, and a better beach, go to Dreams Onyx. If you want a Cancun family resort with golf, watersports, a Flowrider, and a nightclub despite a weak beach, go to Dreams Vista Cancun.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who prioritize a stronger beach experience alongside a lazy river, dual waterparks, and a swim-up bar in a lively Punta Cana setting. Particularly well-suited to families with young children who want wide-ranging water features without needing an on-site golf course or diving program.","whoShouldChooseB":"Active families and couples who want a broader activity menu including golf, diving, windsurfing, a Flowrider, and a nightclub, and are willing to accept a significantly weaker beach in exchange for that variety. Pet owners will also find Vista one of the few family all-inclusives that accommodates their animals.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when rainfall is lowest and crowds are highest. Punta Cana's hurricane season runs June through November, with September the riskiest month. Cancun shares a similar Atlantic hurricane window but benefits from slightly more predictable shoulder-season weather in May and November. Both resorts carry peak-season premium pricing from Christmas through Easter.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, guests have Punta Cana's reef snorkelling, dune-buggy excursions, and deep-sea fishing nearby. At Dreams Vista Cancun, the hotel zone places guests within easy reach of Isla Mujeres day trips, Chichen Itza tours, cenote diving, and Xcaret eco-parks, while on-site golf, windsurfing, and a Flowrider reduce the need to leave the property for activity variety."},"dreams-jade-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Jade and Dreams Onyx are both premium family all-inclusives in the same brand family, but they diverge meaningfully on ratings and setting. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana edges ahead on nearly every metric: overall (9.1 vs 8.8), cleanliness (9.1 vs 8.9), service (9.0 vs 8.8), sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.6), atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.8), and beach (6.5 vs 4.8). That beach gap is the starkest difference — Jade's 4.8 beach score is notably weak for a Mexican Caribbean resort, while Onyx's 6.5 is respectable for Punta Cana. Onyx adds dedicated waterparks for both younger and older kids, making it the stronger choice for families prioritizing water-based entertainment. Jade counters with active-lifestyle amenities Onyx lacks: archery, diving, fishing, heated pool, bicycles, and tennis, giving it more breadth for adventurous families. Both offer lazy rivers, adult pools, teen clubs, and walk-in kids clubs for under-4s at the same price tier, but Onyx delivers a consistently more polished guest experience across the board.","whoShouldChooseA":"Active families who want a broad amenity set including diving, fishing, archery, tennis, and bicycles alongside standard all-inclusive comforts, and who are based in or near Mexico for a shorter transfer. Best suited to guests who prioritize resort activities over beach quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who want the strongest overall guest experience in the Dreams brand, with higher marks across service, cleanliness, sleep quality, and atmosphere, plus dedicated waterparks for kids of all ages and a meaningfully better beach. Ideal for those flying into Punta Cana who want a consistently well-run resort.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations share a similar peak season from December through April when weather is driest and most reliable. Puerto Morelos sees its rainiest stretch from June through October with occasional hurricane risk; Punta Cana's hurricane exposure runs similarly, peaking August through October. For either resort, January through March delivers the most dependable conditions and the highest nightly rates.","activities":"Dreams Jade guests can dive the Mesoamerican Reef — the world's second largest — just offshore, explore the Crococun Zoo and Tres Ríos nature park nearby, or rent bikes along Puerto Morelos's quieter coastline. Dreams Onyx guests are a short drive from Punta Cana's watersports, Scape Park's cenotes and zip lines, and Saona Island catamaran excursions. Both resorts offer on-site evening entertainment, spa services, and lazy river access."},"dreams-estrella-del-mar-mazatlan-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Estrella del Mar Mazatlán and Dreams Onyx Punta Cana are both four-dollar-sign family all-inclusives with nearly identical overall scores (9.0 vs 9.1) and matching food ratings (7.6 each), but they diverge meaningfully in a few areas. Estrella del Mar edges ahead on rooms (9.5 vs 8.7), cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.1), service (9.2 vs 9.0), and value (8.9 vs 8.7), while Onyx counters with a marginally better pool score (7.4 vs 7.3) and a slightly stronger beach (6.5 vs 6.8, though both are modest). The biggest practical difference is the activity and accommodation spread: Estrella del Mar adds a full golf course, yoga classes, and heated pool, making it the stronger pick for adults and golfers; Dreams Onyx adds a teen club and rooms for five or more guests, making it the stronger fit for larger families. Estrella del Mar is in Mazatlán on Mexico's Pacific coast, a less-trafficked destination; Onyx sits in the well-developed Punta Cana corridor of the Dominican Republic.","whoShouldChooseA":"Golfers, couples, or families who want an exceptionally well-appointed Pacific Mexico all-inclusive with outstanding rooms, a full golf course, yoga, and a heated pool, and who prefer a quieter, less touristy destination than the crowded Caribbean resort strips.","whoShouldChooseB":"Larger families, especially those needing rooms for five or more guests, who want a full-featured Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a teen club, kids waterpark, and the familiar infrastructure of the Punta Cana resort corridor.","whenToVisit":"Mazatlán's dry, sunny season runs November through April, making those months ideal for Estrella del Mar; summer brings heat and occasional Pacific hurricane risk. Punta Cana's best weather also falls November through April, with peak crowds around Christmas and Easter. Both resorts share a similar sweet spot: January through March offers good weather, reasonable rates, and thinner holiday crowds at either destination.","activities":"At Estrella del Mar, the 27-hole golf course is the standout, supplemented by a spa, lazy river, waterparks for all ages, yoga, and evening entertainment; Mazatlán's historic Old Town and Malecón boardwalk are accessible nearby. At Dreams Onyx, guests have lazy rivers, dual waterparks, swim-up bars, teen and kids clubs, and a spa, with Punta Cana excursions including dune buggies, catamaran trips, and cenote tours readily available."},"dreams-karibana-cartagena-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Karibana Cartagena Golf & Spa Resort is a Colombian all-inclusive on the outskirts of Cartagena, distinguished by an on-site golf course, pet-friendly policy, and exceptionally high room (9.0) and cleanliness (9.1) scores, though its beach (4.5) and pool (6.9) ratings lag noticeably behind. Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a Dominican Republic all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a stronger overall score (9.1 vs 8.9), meaningfully better food (7.6 vs 7.0), beach (6.5 vs 4.5), pool (7.4 vs 6.9), and atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.8) ratings, plus a waterpark for both young and older kids, a lazy river, teen club, and swim-up bar. Karibana wins on rooms and offers golf and pet access that Onyx cannot match, but Onyx delivers a more rounded beach resort experience with superior water amenities and broader family programming. If you want a distinctive Colombian setting, an on-site golf course, and exceptional accommodations, choose Karibana. If you want a stronger beach, better food, waterparks, and a full family activity slate in the Dominican Republic, choose Onyx.","whoShouldChooseA":"Golfers, pet owners, and families who prioritize stunning room quality and a unique South American all-inclusive setting over beach quality. Ideal for those who want to pair a resort stay with exploring the historic walled city of Cartagena nearby.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with kids of all ages who want a well-rounded Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, a teen club, swim-up bar, and one of Punta Cana's reliably better beaches, all at a slightly higher overall guest satisfaction score.","whenToVisit":"Cartagena's dry season runs December through April, making those months ideal for Karibana despite its modest beach rating. Punta Cana is a year-round destination with its peak season also December through April; Onyx sees its best beach and weather conditions then. Both resorts share a Caribbean-adjacent hurricane window of June through November, with September the riskiest month for Punta Cana.","activities":"Karibana guests can golf on-site, explore the UNESCO-listed walled city of Cartagena, and take boat trips to the Rosario Islands. Onyx guests have waterparks, a lazy river, and a swim-up bar on property, with excursions to Saona Island, dune buggy tours, and catamaran snorkelling trips readily available from Punta Cana. Both resorts offer spa facilities, evening entertainment, and kids club programming."},"dreams-macao-beach-punta-cana-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Macao Beach Punta Cana and Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa are both family-focused Dominican all-inclusives at the same price tier with identical food scores (7.6), pool scores (7.4), and value scores (8.7), making the differences more targeted than sweeping. Macao Beach holds a clear edge in beach quality (7.8 vs 6.5, a 1.3-point gap) and location (8.9 vs 8.6), which reflects its position on the quieter, less-developed Macao Beach. Macao also adds meaningful activity depth that Onyx lacks: archery, yoga, diving, snorkelling, tennis, watersports equipment rentals, and a nightclub. Onyx counters with a spa, slightly better sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.9), and a marginally higher overall score (9.1 vs 9.0). Both have waterparks for kids and teens, lazy rivers, and adult pools. In practice, Macao Beach is the more activity-rich, beach-forward resort, while Onyx is the better choice for guests who prioritise spa access and quieter evenings over watersports and nightlife.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and active couples who want a strong beach, a wide activity roster including diving, snorkelling, tennis, archery, and yoga, plus a nightclub and watersports rentals. The higher beach score and Macao's less-crowded shoreline make it the better pick for guests who genuinely want to be outdoors.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who want a solid all-inclusive with solid waterpark facilities and a spa on-site, and who are less focused on beach quality or a broad activity program. The marginally higher overall and sleep quality scores suggest a quieter, more restful atmosphere than Macao Beach.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in Punta Cana, where the driest and calmest conditions run from December through April. Shoulder months of May and November offer lower rates with mostly manageable weather. Peak hurricane season runs July through October, with September being the highest-risk month. Macao Beach's more exposed Atlantic-facing shoreline can see choppier surf during rougher weather periods.","activities":"Both resorts offer on-site waterparks, lazy rivers, kids and teen clubs, and evening entertainment. Dreams Macao Beach adds diving, snorkelling, watersports rentals, tennis, archery, and yoga on-site. Off-property, guests at either resort can access ATV tours through the Macao area, dune buggy excursions, Scape Park, deep-sea fishing, and day trips to Saona Island, all easily arranged through resort concierge desks."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-vallarta-bay-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa and Dreams Vallarta Bay Resort & Spa are both $$$$, family-focused Dreams properties with kids clubs, teen clubs, adult pools, swim-up bars, buffets, and evening entertainment, but they diverge meaningfully in location, amenities, and ratings. Onyx sits in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, and scores higher overall (9.1 vs 8.9), with better pool (7.4 vs 6.9), atmosphere (7.4 vs 7.1), beach (6.5 vs 6.0), value (8.7 vs 8.5), and sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.7) ratings. Its standout differentiator is a lazy river and dedicated waterpark for both little and big kids, making it a stronger pure waterpark-style family resort. Vallarta Bay is set in Puerto Vallarta, Mexico, and compensates with a more active amenity set: diving, tennis, fishing, a nightclub, pool slides, and a heated pool. Rooms score marginally higher at Vallarta Bay (8.8 vs 8.7). Onyx is the better choice for young families who want splash-focused infrastructure; Vallarta Bay suits active families and couples who want watersports, a nightclub, and the Pacific Mexico setting.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who want a Dominican Republic all-inclusive built around water play, with a lazy river, waterparks for all ages, and strong overall ratings for cleanliness, service, and sleep quality at a slightly better value score than its Mexican counterpart.","whoShouldChooseB":"Active families and couples in Puerto Vallarta who want a broader activity roster beyond the pool, including diving, tennis, fishing, a nightclub, and a heated pool, and who are happy to trade a slightly lower pool and beach rating for Pacific Mexico scenery and more diverse programming.","whenToVisit":"Punta Cana enjoys warm, dry conditions from December through April, making winter the prime window for Dreams Onyx; hurricane season peaks September to October. Puerto Vallarta's dry season runs November through April, with reliably sunny skies and calm seas, while summer brings higher humidity and occasional tropical showers. Both resorts sit in their respective destinations' classic high seasons during the same winter months.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, guests can explore the Bavaro beach strip, take excursions to Saona Island, or visit nearby Punta Cana's golf courses and cenotes. At Dreams Vallarta Bay, the surrounding Puerto Vallarta area offers whale watching (December to March), zip-lining in the Sierra Madre foothills, Marietas Islands snorkelling, Old Town Vallarta's Malecón boardwalk, and boat tours along Banderas Bay, giving it a richer off-site excursion menu."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-riviera-cancun-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa and Dreams Riviera Cancun Resort & Spa are both large family all-inclusives in the same brand and price tier, but key differences emerge in beach quality, activities, and destination. Onyx sits in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, and scores notably higher on beach (6.5 vs. 4.8), overall rating (9.1 vs. 8.8), and value (8.7 vs. 8.5). It adds waterparks for both younger and older kids and rooms for five or more guests, making it the stronger pick for larger families. Dreams Riviera Cancun is in Puerto Morelos, Mexico, and counters with a pool slide, heated pool, diving, nightclub, and room service — amenities Onyx lacks. Its beach score of 4.8 is a meaningful weakness. Both resorts share lazy rivers, teen clubs, kids clubs for under-4s, swim-up bars, and open-seating restaurants. Food scores are nearly identical (7.6 vs. 7.5). If beach quality and waterpark coverage matter most, Onyx wins; if diving, a nightclub, and Mexican proximity appeal, Riviera Cancun has the edge.","whoShouldChooseA":"Larger families, including groups of five or more, who prioritize a strong beach, dual waterparks, and high overall satisfaction scores in a Dominican Republic setting. Also suits those who want excellent sleep quality and cleanliness ratings without sacrificing value.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who want a Mexican Caribbean base with added amenities like diving, a nightclub, a heated pool, and a pool slide, and who are less concerned about beach quality. Suits couples or families with teens who want more activity variety and the convenience of room service.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when rainfall is low and humidity manageable. Punta Cana's hurricane season runs June through November, with September the riskiest month. Puerto Morelos shares a similar risk window. Shoulder months of May and November offer lower prices at both resorts with generally acceptable weather. Summer school holidays drive up demand and pricing at both properties.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, guests can use the waterparks, lazy river, and adult pool, or explore Punta Cana's wider strip of excursions including dune buggies, zip-lining, and catamaran tours. At Dreams Riviera Cancun, guests can dive directly through the resort, and Puerto Morelos sits minutes from the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef, making snorkelling and reef diving accessible. Both offer evening entertainment, spas, and teen and kids programming on-site."},"breathless-riviera-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Riviera Cancun and Dreams Onyx are both four-dollar-sign all-inclusives with identical food scores (7.6), pool scores (7.4), and atmosphere scores (7.4), but they diverge sharply in purpose and setting. Breathless is an adults-only property in Mexico's Caracol area built around nightlife and socializing, with a nightclub and heated pool but a notably weak beach score of 4.8 compared to Dreams Onyx's 6.5. Dreams Onyx is a family resort in Punta Cana with a waterpark for both small and big kids, a lazy river, kids club for under-4s, teen club, babysitting, and rooms that sleep five or more. Dreams edges Breathless on overall score (9.1 vs 8.8), service (9.0 vs 8.9), sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.4), and value (8.7 vs 8.4), while Breathless leads on room score (8.9 vs 8.7). If you want a lively adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with a nightclub and no children, choose Breathless. If you want a family-first Dominican Republic resort with strong kids infrastructure and a better beach, choose Dreams Onyx.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples and groups who want a social, nightlife-oriented all-inclusive in Mexico's Riviera Cancun with a nightclub, swim-up bar, and heated pool, and who prioritize exceptional rooms and cleanliness over beach quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families of all sizes, including those with toddlers and teenagers, who want a well-rounded Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, dedicated kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and large-capacity rooms in Punta Cana.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April. Riviera Cancun's drier, breezier climate makes it slightly more comfortable in shoulder months like May and November. Punta Cana is warm year-round but sees elevated hurricane risk August through October. For either resort, January through March delivers the most reliable weather and the most vibrant atmosphere.","activities":"At Breathless Riviera Cancun, guests can use the spa, gym, and nightclub, and access nearby cenotes, Mayan ruins at Tulum or Cobá, and deep-sea fishing. At Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana, families can enjoy on-site waterparks and a lazy river, plus off-site excursions to Saona Island, dune-buggy tours, and snorkeling at natural pools. Both resorts offer evening entertainment and swim-up bars for in-resort downtime."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-baby-beach-aruba":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark, lazy river, kids club for under 4s, teen club, babysitting, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment, scoring a strong 9.1 overall but trailing on beach (6.5) and food (7.6). Secrets Baby Beach Aruba is a compact adults-only all-inclusive on Aruba's southern tip in San Nicolas, with a significantly better beach score (8.5 vs 6.5), superior food (8.2 vs 7.6), and outstanding room (9.4 vs 8.7), cleanliness (9.5 vs 9.1), service (9.3 vs 9.0), and sleep quality (9.3 vs 9.1) ratings. Dreams Onyx wins on overall score (9.1 vs 8.6) and delivers far more in terms of family infrastructure and entertainment programming. Secrets Baby Beach trades breadth of amenities for refinement and a genuinely better beach experience. If you want a fully loaded Dominican family resort with waterparks, kids clubs, and evening entertainment at a high overall rating, choose Dreams Onyx. If you want a polished adults-only Aruban retreat with a better beach, exceptional rooms, and superior food and service scores, choose Secrets Baby Beach.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a large Dominican all-inclusive packed with waterparks, a lazy river, multiple kids clubs, babysitting, and evening entertainment. The strong overall score of 9.1 and rooms that accommodate five or more guests make it well-suited to larger family groups.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who prioritize a superior beach, refined rooms, and excellent service over entertainment programming. With a 9.4 room score, 9.5 cleanliness, and 8.5 beach rating, Secrets Baby Beach rewards guests seeking a quieter, more polished adults-only escape in Aruba.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana is best visited December through April when the Dominican Republic's dry season brings reliable sunshine and lower humidity. Secrets Baby Beach benefits from Aruba's position outside the hurricane belt, making it a strong year-round destination, though December through April offers the driest and coolest conditions for both resorts.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can enjoy onsite waterparks, a lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, and evening entertainment, with Punta Cana excursions including dune buggies, catamaran trips, and zip-lining nearby. Secrets Baby Beach sits near Aruba's southern coast, giving guests access to world-class windsurfing at Sorobon Beach, snorkeling, flamingo beach visits on Renaissance Island, and jeep safari tours across Aruba's rugged interior."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-riviera-cancun-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a kids club, teen club, waterparks, lazy river, babysitting, adult pool, and rooms for five or more guests, earning a strong overall rating of 9.1 against Secrets Riviera Cancun's 8.6. Secrets Riviera Cancun is an adults-only all-inclusive in Mexico's Caracol area with a nightclub and a notably higher room rating of 9.0 versus Dreams Onyx's 8.7, but its beach rating of 4.8 is a significant weakness compared to Dreams Onyx's 6.5. Dreams Onyx wins on overall score, beach, pool, and family infrastructure, while Secrets edges it on rooms, cleanliness, and service. The most meaningful practical gap is the family-versus-adults-only divide: Dreams Onyx has the waterparks, lazy river, and kids programming for multigenerational travel, while Secrets trades all of that for a quieter, nightclub-equipped adults escape. If you want a high-rated Dominican Republic family all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, and broad kids programming, go to Dreams Onyx. If you want an adults-only Mexican retreat with superior rooms and a nightclub but a notably weak beach, go to Secrets Riviera Cancun.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a high-scoring Dominican all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, a kids club for under-fours, a teen club, babysitting, and rooms large enough for five or more guests on a solid Punta Cana beach.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want a quieter, adults-only Mexican all-inclusive with upscale rooms, a nightclub, and strong service scores, and who are willing to accept a significantly below-average beach in exchange for a more refined, child-free atmosphere.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in peak Caribbean and Mexican winter-sun territory. Punta Cana's dry season runs December through April, with hurricane risk peaking August through October. The Riviera Maya shares a similar pattern, with dry and settled weather from November through April. Both carry a premium in peak winter months; shoulder seasons of May and November offer lower rates with generally manageable weather.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can enjoy Punta Cana's nearby golf courses, catamaran excursions, snorkelling trips, and Bavaro's busy beach strip. Secrets Riviera Cancun sits near the Riviera Maya's cenotes, ancient Mayan ruins including Tulum and Cobá, jungle zip-lining, and the coral reef snorkelling of Puerto Morelos. Both resorts offer on-site spa treatments, swim-up bars, and evening entertainment programs."},"dreams-aventuras-riviera-maya-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Aventuras Riviera Maya sits in Puerto Aventuras, Mexico, a quieter marina enclave on the Riviera Maya, while Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, on a more established resort beach corridor. Onyx scores higher on almost every measurable dimension: overall 9.1 vs 8.9, food 7.6 vs 7.0, beach 6.5 vs 5.3, pool 7.4 vs 6.6, atmosphere 7.4 vs 6.9, and sleep quality 9.1 vs 8.6. Aventuras counters with diving, snorkelling, and yoga classes, plus a notably strong location score of 8.3 given its access to cenotes, ruins, and the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef. Onyx adds a teen club and a lazy river, giving it a slight edge for families with older kids. Both share waterparks for all ages, kids clubs from under 4, babysitting, swim-up bars, and large-group rooms. Aventuras suits adventure-oriented families drawn to Mexico's natural and cultural attractions; Onyx delivers a more polished, beach-forward Dominican experience with stronger across-the-board ratings.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a Mexican all-inclusive with diving, snorkelling, and yoga on-site, and easy access to cenotes, Mayan ruins, and the Mesoamerican reef. Best for those who plan to leave the resort regularly and want adventure as much as poolside relaxation.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families seeking a higher-rated Dominican Republic all-inclusive with stronger food, beach, pool, and sleep quality scores, plus a lazy river and teen club. Ideal for those who want a polished, stay-on-property experience with broad amenities and consistently strong guest satisfaction.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak in the dry season from December through April, when rainfall is minimal and humidity manageable. Puerto Aventuras and Punta Cana share similar hurricane exposure from June through November, with September being the riskiest month for both. For best beach and pool conditions at either resort, aim for January through March.","activities":"Dreams Aventuras guests can dive and snorkel the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef, explore nearby cenotes and Tulum ruins, or sail out of Puerto Aventuras marina. Dreams Onyx guests are close to Bavaro's watersports, Saona Island day trips, and Punta Cana zip-lining. Both resorts offer on-site evening entertainment, waterparks, and spa facilities for days spent entirely on property."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-rose-hall-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a premium Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark for both little and big kids, a dedicated under-4s club, adult pool, lazy river, and swim-up bar, rated notably higher across nearly every category than its Jamaican counterpart. Dreams Rose Hall sits in Montego Bay at a significantly lower price point and adds tennis, a golf course, and a nightclub, but trails Onyx on overall score (8.5 vs 9.1), food (7.4 vs 7.6), pool (7.1 vs 7.4), atmosphere (7.1 vs 7.4), room (8.2 vs 8.7), cleanliness (8.7 vs 9.1), and service (8.7 vs 9.0). Onyx also includes free Wi-Fi where Rose Hall charges for it. The beach ratings are close but both modest (6.5 vs 6.0). If you want a higher-rated Dominican family all-inclusive with a proper waterpark, infant programming, and stronger service at a premium price, go to Dreams Onyx. If you want a budget-friendlier Jamaican family resort with golf, tennis, and a nightclub in Montego Bay, go to Dreams Rose Hall.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages, including infants, who want a high-rated Punta Cana all-inclusive with a full waterpark, dedicated under-4s club, adult pool, and consistently strong service and cleanliness at a premium price point.","whoShouldChooseB":"Budget-conscious families with older kids or teenagers who want a Jamaican all-inclusive near Montego Bay with golf, tennis, a nightclub, and solid core amenities at a meaningfully lower price point than comparable Dominican resorts.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations share similar Caribbean seasonality. Peak dry season runs December through April for both Punta Cana and Montego Bay, with lower humidity and reduced rainfall. Hurricane season runs June through November for both, with September and October carrying the highest risk. Shoulder months of May and early December offer a balance of lower rates and reasonable weather at either property.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can explore Punta Cana's broader resort strip, take excursions to Indigenous Eyes Ecological Park, or book cave and catamaran tours. Dreams Rose Hall guests have access to the adjacent golf course, Montego Bay's Hip Strip, Dunn's River Falls day trips, and river tubing excursions. Both resorts offer beach and pool activities, evening entertainment, and spa treatments on property."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-marigot-bay-st-lucia":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a kids club, teen club, waterparks, lazy river, adult pool, swim-up bar, evening entertainment, and babysitting — a full-service Dominican Republic beach resort rated 9.1 overall with a beach score of 6.5. Zoëtry Marigot Bay St. Lucia is a boutique St. Lucia all-inclusive set in the dramatic Marigot Bay, rated 8.6 overall, with a beach score of just 2.5, reflecting its marina-bay setting rather than a traditional sandy beach. Zoëtry scores higher on food (8.6 vs 7.6), atmosphere (8.6 vs 7.4), and sleep quality (9.2 vs 9.1), while Dreams Onyx wins on beach access and sheer activity volume. Dreams Onyx is a sprawling, amenity-rich resort built for families with children of all ages; Zoëtry Marigot Bay is a quieter, more intimate property where the scenery and cuisine carry the experience. Guests who need waterparks and kids clubs should choose Dreams Onyx; guests who prioritize food, ambiance, and a stunning bay setting over beach access should choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a large, activity-packed Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, a kids club, teen club, babysitting, and evening entertainment on a recognizable Punta Cana resort strip.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and small families with older children who want a boutique, food-forward St. Lucia all-inclusive in a spectacular marina-bay setting, and who prioritize atmosphere, cuisine, and tranquility over beach access.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in reliably warm Caribbean destinations. Punta Cana's peak season runs December through April, with hurricane season peaking August through October. St. Lucia's dry season is January through April, with the wettest months from June through November. Both destinations see elevated prices over winter holidays. For value, consider shoulder months like May or November at either property.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, families can enjoy waterparks, a lazy river, swim-up bar, watersports, and evening entertainment shows, with Punta Cana's broader resort strip nearby. At Zoëtry Marigot Bay, guests can fish, use the gym, and explore the bay by boat, with Marigot Bay's sailing scene and the lush St. Lucia interior — including the Pitons, sulfur springs, and rainforest hikes — easily accessible for day excursions."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-wild-orchid-montego-bay":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a kids club, teen club, waterparks for both age groups, babysitting, lazy river, adult pool, and rooms that sleep five or more, scoring a strong 9.1 overall. Secrets Wild Orchid Montego Bay is an adults-only all-inclusive in Jamaica with a casino, nightclub, diving, tennis, room service, and a lazy river, scoring 8.6 overall. Dreams Onyx edges ahead on overall score (9.1 vs 8.6), value (8.7 vs 8.4), and sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.8), while Secrets Wild Orchid leads on food (7.9 vs 7.6), beach (6.8 vs 6.5), atmosphere (7.7 vs 7.4), location (8.9 vs 8.6), and room quality (8.9 vs 8.7). The core split is family infrastructure versus adults-only sophistication: Dreams Onyx is built around keeping families of all ages occupied in the Dominican Republic, while Secrets Wild Orchid delivers a more polished, couple-oriented Jamaican experience with a casino, nightclub, and diving program.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a large Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a kids club, teen club, babysitting, lazy river, and rooms that sleep five or more, all at a strong value rating of 8.7.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want a refined, adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a casino, nightclub, diving, tennis, room service, and a slightly superior food and room experience in a livelier atmosphere.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations share a similar Caribbean peak season from mid-December through April, when rainfall is lowest and humidity most manageable. Punta Cana and Montego Bay both see elevated hurricane risk from August through October. Shoulder months of May and November offer lower prices with generally acceptable weather at both properties.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, guests can use the resort waterparks, lazy river, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment program, with Punta Cana's excursion market offering dune buggies, catamaran trips, and zip-lining nearby. At Secrets Wild Orchid, diving, tennis, and the casino keep guests busy on-site, while Montego Bay offers close access to the Luminous Lagoon, Dunn's River Falls, and Rose Hall Great House."},"breathless-montego-bay-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Montego Bay is an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive on the Montego Bay strip with a nightclub, spa, tennis, and swim-up bar, built around a lively social atmosphere for couples and groups. Dreams Onyx is a family-focused Dominican Republic all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a kids club for under-4s, a teen club, lazy river, waterparks for both age groups, babysitting, and rooms that sleep five or more. The numbers tell a clear story: Dreams Onyx outperforms Breathless across nearly every measurable category, posting a 9.1 overall versus 8.5, a 9.1 on cleanliness versus 8.9, a 9.0 on service versus 8.7, and a 9.1 on sleep quality versus 8.3. The beach gap is notable too, with Dreams Onyx rating 6.5 against Breathless's 5.5. Where Breathless holds its ground is in value at 8.3, though Dreams Onyx still edges it out at 8.7. The core split is simple: one resort is a nightclub-anchored adults retreat in Jamaica, the other is a polished, high-scoring Dominican family operation.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples, friend groups, or solo travelers who want a lively Jamaican all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a nightclub, evening entertainment, and a social atmosphere. Best suited to those who prioritize the Jamaica destination and an adult-focused energy over the broadest possible amenity set.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of any age who want a well-run Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and rooms that fit five or more. The consistently high service and cleanliness scores make it a reliable, low-stress choice for parents.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in the Caribbean's peak dry season from December through April, when rainfall is lowest and conditions are most reliable. Jamaica and the Dominican Republic share similar hurricane exposure from June through November, with September the riskiest month for both. For Breathless Montego Bay, January and February offer the most settled weather. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana performs well across the dry season, with March and April offering good value before spring break pricing kicks in.","activities":"At Breathless Montego Bay, guests can use the spa, tennis courts, and swim-up bar, explore the Hip Strip nearby, take excursions to Dunn's River Falls, or arrange river rafting and boat tours out of Montego Bay. At Dreams Onyx, on-site options include the waterparks, lazy river, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment, while Punta Cana's surrounding area offers dune buggy tours, catamaran trips, zip-lining, and day visits to Saona Island."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-playa-esmeralda-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx and Dreams Playa Esmeralda are both four-dollar-sign Dominican Republic family all-inclusives in the Dreams brand, with identical food scores (7.6), near-identical value ratings (8.7 each), and very close service and cleanliness marks. The differences lie in specific strengths. Onyx scores higher on pool (7.4 vs 7.1) and backs that up with a lazy river, adult pool, swim-up bar, waterpark for little kids, and waterpark for big kids — a meaningfully deeper aquatic amenity set. Playa Esmeralda counters with a significantly better beach score (8.3 vs 6.5), higher room rating (9.2 vs 8.7), better service (9.2 vs 9.0), and a slightly higher cleanliness score (9.3 vs 9.1). Onyx sits in the more developed Punta Cana strip; Playa Esmeralda is in quieter El Cedro with a location score of 9.0 versus Onyx's 8.6. If you want water slides, a lazy river, and swim-up bar in Punta Cana, choose Onyx. If you want a better beach, nicer rooms, and a quieter setting, choose Playa Esmeralda.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with younger and older kids who want maximum on-property water attractions — lazy river, waterparks, swim-up bar, and a teen club — in the heart of the well-connected Punta Cana resort zone, and are willing to trade a weaker beach score for those pool-area amenities.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who prioritize a standout beach (8.3), well-appointed rooms (9.2), and a quieter, less crowded setting in El Cedro, and don't need an elaborate waterpark setup to have a great stay.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from the Dominican Republic's dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is low and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. July and August are popular but humid. Hurricane season peaks September and October, when prices drop but weather risk rises. Either resort delivers reliable sun from late November through mid-April.","activities":"Both resorts offer kids clubs, teen clubs, babysitting, spas, gyms, and buffet dining without reservation requirements. Dreams Onyx adds waterparks, a lazy river, a swim-up bar, and an adult pool for more on-site variety. Off-property, both resorts provide access to the Dominican Republic's classic excursions: catamaran snorkelling trips, dune buggy tours, zip-lining, and day trips to Saona Island."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-st-james-montego-bay":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a kids club, teen club, waterparks, lazy river, babysitting, and rooms that sleep five or more, scoring a strong 9.1 overall and 8.7 for value. Secrets St. James Montego Bay is an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a casino, tennis, diving, nightclub, and heated pool, scoring 8.5 overall with a notably higher food rating of 7.9 versus Dreams Onyx's 7.6. Dreams Onyx leads on overall score (9.1 vs 8.5), cleanliness (9.1 vs 9.0), service (9.0 vs 8.9), and value (8.7 vs 8.4), while Secrets St. James edges ahead on food (7.9 vs 7.6), beach (6.8 vs 6.5), atmosphere (7.7 vs 7.4), location (8.9 vs 8.6), and room quality (8.8 vs 8.7). The fundamental split is family infrastructure versus an adults-only lifestyle experience with casino, diving, and tennis in a Jamaican setting.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a well-rounded Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and rooms large enough for five or more, all at strong value for a four-dollar-sign property.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a casino, nightclub, diving, tennis, and a slightly more refined dining experience in a property with a lively but sophisticated atmosphere.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when rainfall is lowest and demand highest, with prices rising accordingly. Punta Cana's hurricane season runs June through November, with September and October carrying the most risk. Montego Bay shares a similar pattern, though Jamaica's north coast is somewhat more sheltered. Shoulder months of May and early December offer a balance of good weather and lower rates at both resorts.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can enjoy Punta Cana's watersports, nearby Scape Park, Indigenous Eyes Ecological Reserve, and day trips to Saona Island. Secrets St. James sits in Montego Bay, giving guests access to diving, tennis on-site, plus nearby Rose Hall Great House, Dunn's River Falls excursions, Montego Bay Marine Park snorkelling, and the Doctor's Cave Beach strip a short ride away."},"breathless-cancun-soul-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Cancun Soul is an adults-only all-inclusive in Puerto Morelos, Mexico, with a nightclub, swim-up bar, spa, and evening entertainment, positioned as a lively lifestyle resort with standout room ratings (9.1) and cleanliness (9.3) but softer scores for beach (7.8) and pool (7.4). Dreams Onyx is a family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a broader amenity set including a kids club, teen club, lazy river, waterparks for both ages, babysitting, and rooms for five or more guests. Dreams Onyx edges Breathless on overall score (9.1 vs 8.4), service (9.0 vs 8.8), sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.5), and value (8.7 vs 8.3), while Breathless wins on room rating (9.1 vs 8.7) and beach (7.8 vs 6.5). The core split is adults-only Mexico lifestyle resort versus a well-rounded Dominican Republic family property with water-focused programming for kids. If you want a lively, design-forward adults-only resort near Cancun with a nightclub and strong room quality, choose Breathless. If you want a high-scoring family Dominican all-inclusive with waterparks, kids and teen clubs, and superior overall guest satisfaction, choose Dreams Onyx.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or groups who want a lively, nightclub-equipped Mexican all-inclusive near Cancun with excellent room quality, strong cleanliness scores, and an energetic atmosphere without children present.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of all ages who want a high-scoring Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a kids club, teen club, babysitting, rooms for five or more, and consistently strong service and sleep quality ratings.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in peak Caribbean sun belt destinations. Puerto Morelos and Cancun are driest from December through April, with hurricane season risk rising from August through October. Punta Cana shares a similar pattern, with January through March being the driest and most reliable months. Both carry premium pricing over the winter holiday window; shoulder months of May and November offer better value at either property.","activities":"Breathless Cancun guests can explore Puerto Morelos's nearby reef, one of the largest in the world, with snorkelling and diving excursions readily available, plus cenote tours and day trips to Tulum and Playa del Carmen. Dreams Onyx guests have access to Punta Cana's watersports scene, dune buggy excursions, zip-lining, and day trips to Saona Island, with on-site waterparks and a lazy river keeping younger guests fully occupied without leaving the resort."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-sands-cancun-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, with a waterpark for both little and big kids, a teen club, lazy river, adult pool, swim-up bar, babysitting, gym, spa, and evening entertainment. Dreams Sands Cancun is a family all-inclusive on the Cancun hotel zone strip with a kids club, lazy river, and buffet, but a noticeably thinner amenity set. The ratings tell the story clearly: Onyx outscores Sands across nearly every category, including overall (9.1 vs 8.5), food (7.6 vs 6.9), pool (7.4 vs 6.0), atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.7), room (8.7 vs 7.8), cleanliness (9.1 vs 8.5), and value (8.7 vs 8.1). Both share an identical beach rating of 6.5. Onyx also accommodates groups with rooms for five or more guests. If you want a fuller-featured Dominican family all-inclusive with superior ratings across the board and a waterpark, go to Dreams Onyx. If a Cancun address is the priority and a leaner amenity offering is acceptable, Dreams Sands is the option.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a highly rated, amenity-rich Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark for all ages, a teen club, swim-up bar, spa, and evening entertainment, and who may need larger rooms to accommodate groups of five or more.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who specifically want a Cancun, Mexico base, perhaps to combine the resort stay with nearby attractions like Chichen Itza or cenotes, and are comfortable with a more limited on-site amenity offering at a similar price point.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in the Caribbean basin where peak season runs December through April, bringing dry weather and lower humidity. Punta Cana and Cancun share a similar hurricane window from June through November, with September the riskiest month at both. Shoulder months of May and early December offer lower rates with generally decent weather at either property.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, guests can use the waterpark, lazy river, adult pool, and spa on-site, while Punta Cana offers nearby dune buggies, deep-sea fishing, and catamaran excursions. At Dreams Sands Cancun, the hotel zone location gives easy access to Isla Mujeres day trips, cenote swimming, Chichen Itza tours, and Cancun's nightlife strip, supplementing the resort's more modest on-site activity program."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-sapphire-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark for both little and big kids, a lazy river, swim-up bar, adult pool, and rooms that accommodate five or more guests, earning a strong overall rating of 9.1 versus Dreams Sapphire's 8.7. Dreams Sapphire Resort & Spa sits in Puerto Morelos, Mexico, and trades the waterpark and lazy river for diving, snorkelling, fishing, yoga, tennis, and a nightclub. On the ratings that matter most to families, Onyx leads across the board: beach (6.5 vs 5.0), pool (7.4 vs 6.7), atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.9), and value (8.7 vs 8.4). Sapphire counters with a broader activity roster suited to older kids and active adults. If you want a waterpark-equipped Dominican family all-inclusive with the best pool and beach scores, go to Dreams Onyx. If you want a Mexico all-inclusive with diving, snorkelling, tennis, and a nightclub near the Riviera Maya, go to Dreams Sapphire.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a high-rated Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, large-group rooms, and strong scores across overall experience, cleanliness, and sleep quality at a solid value.","whoShouldChooseB":"Active families and couples with older kids who want a Mexico all-inclusive near the Riviera Maya with diving, snorkelling, fishing, yoga, tennis, and a nightclub rounding out the evening, even if pool and beach ratings trail Onyx.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in peak sun-and-sea territory. Punta Cana's dry season runs December through April, making those months ideal for Dreams Onyx. Puerto Morelos shares the Riviera Maya's best weather from November through May. Both destinations see hurricane-season risk July through October, with September the most active month for both the Dominican Republic and Mexico's Caribbean coast.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can ride the lazy river, splash through the waterpark, swim in the adult pool, and enjoy evening entertainment on the Punta Cana strip, with nearby golf and excursions to Saona Island. Dreams Sapphire guests can dive, snorkel, fish, take yoga classes, and play tennis in Puerto Morelos, with the Mesoamerican Reef, Tulum ruins, and Cancun all within easy reach."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-mirabel-cancun-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx is a large Punta Cana family all-inclusive built around extensive water facilities — a lazy river, waterparks for both age groups, a kids club for under-4s, a teen club, and babysitting — with strong overall (9.1) and cleanliness (9.1) scores but notably weaker food (7.6) and beach (6.5) ratings. Secrets Mirabel is an adults-only Cancun property where the numbers tell a different story: food climbs to 8.2, beach improves to 7.3, rooms reach 9.1, and sleep quality hits 9.2, reflecting a quieter, more polished environment without the noise and logistics of a family resort. Location scores are close (8.6 vs 9.0), but the atmosphere gap (7.4 vs 8.0) signals that Secrets Mirabel delivers a more refined feel. Dreams Onyx wins on breadth of family amenities and rooms accommodating five or more guests; Secrets Mirabel wins on food quality, room comfort, and the adults-only tranquility that its ratings consistently support across multiple categories.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a Dominican Republic all-inclusive packed with water attractions — lazy river, dual waterparks, a kids club for toddlers, and a teen club — plus babysitting and large-group rooms, and can accept that food and beach ratings trail the overall score.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or groups who want a polished, quieter Cancun all-inclusive with strong food (8.2), excellent room comfort (9.1), high sleep quality (9.2), and a beachfront location, without the activity and noise level that comes with a family-oriented property.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when rainfall is low and humidity manageable. Punta Cana's hurricane season runs June through November, making Dreams Onyx a higher weather-risk choice in late summer. Cancun shares a similar hurricane window but statistically sees fewer direct hits than the Dominican Republic's eastern coast. Shoulder months of May and late November offer lower rates at both resorts with generally acceptable conditions.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests have access to on-site waterparks, a lazy river, snorkelling excursions, and proximity to Punta Cana's Bavaro strip for zip-lining, dune buggy tours, and day trips to Saona Island. Secrets Mirabel guests can snorkel directly from the resort, explore Cancun's Hotel Zone, take day trips to Isla Mujeres or Chichen Itza, and access a broad range of watersports and cenote tours from the Cancun area."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-sunscape-dorado-pacifico-ixtapa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a premium Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Punta Cana rated 9.1 overall, loaded with amenities including a waterpark for little and big kids, lazy river, teen club, kids club for under-4s, adult pool, swim-up bar, spa, gym, babysitting, evening entertainment, and multiple restaurants requiring no reservations. Sunscape Dorado Pacifico Ixtapa is a more budget-friendly Mexican family all-inclusive on Ixtapa's Pacific coast rated 8.6 overall, with a beach as its primary listed amenity and a notably leaner facilities profile. Dreams Onyx outscores Sunscape on nearly every metric: food (7.6 vs 6.4), pool (7.4 vs 6.2), atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.3), room (8.7 vs 8.2), and sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.0). Sunscape holds a slight edge on beach (6.8 vs 6.5) and location (8.8 vs 8.6) and costs less. Dreams Onyx is the clear choice for families wanting a feature-rich Caribbean resort; Sunscape suits travelers prioritizing value and Pacific Mexico over resort amenities.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a fully loaded Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, teen and toddler clubs, babysitting, adult pool, spa, and evening entertainment, and are willing to pay a premium for a higher-rated, amenity-dense resort experience in Punta Cana.","whoShouldChooseB":"Budget-conscious families or couples drawn specifically to Ixtapa's Pacific Mexico setting who prioritize location and value over resort amenities, and are comfortable with a more stripped-back all-inclusive experience at a lower price point.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana is best November through April when the Dominican Republic's dry season delivers reliable sunshine and calmer seas. Sunscape Dorado Pacifico in Ixtapa sits on Mexico's Pacific coast, where the dry season runs November through April as well; avoid the summer rainy season from June through October when Pacific swells and tropical storms can disrupt beach conditions at both destinations.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests have waterparks, a lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, gym, and evening entertainment on-site, with Punta Cana's broader strip of excursions, cenotes, and reef snorkeling nearby. Sunscape Dorado Pacifico guests are steps from Ixtapa's beach and close to Zihuatanejo's historic town center, sport fishing, scuba diving, and the Ixtapa Island nature reserve accessible by short ferry."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-montego-bay-jamaica":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark, lazy river, kids club for under-4s, teen club, adult pool, swim-up bar, babysitting, and evening entertainment. Zoëtry Montego Bay Jamaica is a small adults-only boutique all-inclusive on Montego Bay with no waterpark or kids programming, oriented toward couples seeking quiet and intimacy. The rating gaps tell the story clearly: Dreams Onyx scores significantly higher on beach (6.5 vs 4.0) and pool (7.4 vs 6.7), while Zoëtry edges ahead on food (8.1 vs 7.6) and atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.4). Dreams Onyx leads on overall score (9.1 vs 8.2) and value (8.7 vs 7.9). Dreams Onyx is the better resort for activity-rich family holidays, while Zoëtry trades amenity breadth for a quieter, more refined adults-only experience in Jamaica. If you want a large Dominican family all-inclusive with waterslides, babysitting, and a full entertainment program, choose Dreams Onyx. If you want a small, serene adults-only Jamaican retreat with better food and atmosphere, choose Zoëtry Montego Bay.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a feature-packed Dominican all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, kids club from infancy, teen club, babysitting, and evening entertainment at strong value for a $$$ price point.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or solo travellers who want a quiet, boutique adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive with better food ratings, a refined atmosphere, and an intimate scale, and who can accept a notably weaker beach score of 4.0.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak from December through April when rainfall is lowest and skies are clearest. Punta Cana's hurricane season runs June through November, with September and October the riskiest months. Jamaica shares a similar Atlantic hurricane window. Shoulder months of May and late November offer lower prices with generally manageable weather at both properties.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can use the waterpark, lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, and gym on site, with Punta Cana's wider resort strip offering excursions to Saona Island, dune-buggy tours, and deep-sea fishing nearby. Zoëtry Montego Bay guests are close to Montego Bay's Doctor's Cave Beach, the Hip Strip, Dunn's River Falls day trips, and river tubing excursions in the Jamaican interior."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-tulum-resort-and-beach-club":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark, kids club, teen club, lazy river, swim-up bar, babysitting, evening entertainment, and rooms for groups of five or more, scoring a strong 9.1 overall with standout marks for service (9.0) and sleep quality (9.1). Secrets Tulum is an adults-only all-inclusive in Mexico's Tulum corridor, scoring lower overall at 8.3 but edging ahead on atmosphere (8.5 vs 7.4) and room quality (8.9 vs 8.7), with a notably weaker beach score (5.5 vs 6.5). Dreams Onyx wins on location (8.6 vs 7.8) and value (8.7 vs 7.9), reflecting its broader amenity set for the price. Secrets Tulum's appeal is its adults-only atmosphere and proximity to Tulum's cenotes and ruins, not beach quality or facilities depth. If you want a well-rounded Dominican family resort with waterpark amenities and strong service ratings, go to Dreams Onyx. If you want a quieter, design-conscious adults-only escape near Tulum's cultural attractions, go to Secrets Tulum.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a full-featured Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, lazy river, and evening entertainment at a price point that delivers strong value ratings.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or solo travelers who prioritize a peaceful, atmosphere-driven all-inclusive near Tulum's cenotes and archaeological sites, and who value well-appointed rooms and a refined environment over beach quality or extensive amenities.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in the Caribbean's peak dry season from December through April, when rainfall is lowest and conditions are most reliable. Punta Cana's shoulder months of May and November offer good weather at lower rates. Tulum's summer months bring higher humidity and occasional rain but significantly reduced crowds, making June and early July reasonable for budget-conscious adult travelers.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can enjoy its onsite waterpark, lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, and evening entertainment, with excursions to Saona Island and Hoyo Azul cenote nearby. Secrets Tulum guests have fewer onsite activity options but sit close to the Tulum archaeological zone, Gran Cenote, and Sian Ka'an Biosphere Reserve, making it a natural base for cultural and eco-focused day trips beyond the resort."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-sunscape-dominicus-la-romana":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa and Sunscape Dominicus La Romana are both family-oriented Dominican Republic all-inclusives at the same price tier, but they diverge sharply on amenities, ratings, and atmosphere. Dreams Onyx scores a full point higher overall (9.1 vs 8.1) and leads in nearly every category: food (7.6 vs 6.2), pool (7.4 vs 6.2), atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.2), room (8.7 vs 8.0), cleanliness (9.1 vs 8.5), and service (9.0 vs 8.3). Dreams Onyx is the more infrastructure-heavy resort, packing in a lazy river, adult pool, swim-up bar, spa, gym, babysitting, a kids club for under-4s, evening entertainment, and no-reservation restaurants. Sunscape Dominicus counters with a notably better beach score (8.0 vs 6.5), a quieter La Romana setting, and a more stripped-back amenity list limited mainly to kids and teen clubs and waterparks. Dreams Onyx is the fuller-featured, higher-rated resort; Sunscape Dominicus offers a better beach experience in a calmer coastal enclave but at the cost of on-site programming depth.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a comprehensive, high-rated Punta Cana all-inclusive with a lazy river, swim-up bar, adult pool, spa, babysitting, and evening entertainment under one roof. Particularly strong for families with very young children given the under-4 kids club, no-reservation dining flexibility, and rooms that fit five or more guests.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who prioritize beach quality above all else and prefer a quieter, less programmed Dominican setting near La Romana. A good fit for those happy with a more relaxed pace and a leaner amenity set, and who are willing to accept lower food and pool ratings in exchange for a genuinely better stretch of sand.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in the Dominican Republic and share the same broad seasonal pattern. December through April is peak dry season with the most reliable sunshine and lowest humidity, making it the most popular and most expensive window. May and June offer shoulder-season value before hurricane season peaks July through October. November brings improving conditions and often better rates than high season.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can use the on-site waterparks, lazy river, spa, and gym, with Punta Cana's busy excursion corridor nearby for zip-lining, dune buggy tours, and cenote visits. Sunscape Dominicus guests benefit from the La Romana location, putting them within reach of Altos de Chavón, Casa de Campo's golf courses, and boat trips to Saona Island, one of the Dominican Republic's most visited natural attractions."},"dreams-bahia-mita-surf-and-spa-resort-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Bahia Mita Surf & Spa Resort is a premium Mexican family all-inclusive on the Pacific coast near Punta de Mita, with strong room (9.0), cleanliness (9.2), and service (9.0) scores but a notably weak beach rating (4.8) and modest pool score (7.1), reflecting the surf-oriented coastline rather than a calm swimming beach. Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a higher overall rating (9.1 vs 8.6), a meaningfully better beach score (6.5 vs 4.8), and a significantly broader amenity set including a lazy river, adult pool, waterparks for both age groups, teen club, swim-up bar, and rooms accommodating five or more guests. Bahia Mita wins on room quality and cleanliness, and suits guests drawn to the dramatic Pacific setting and boutique Riviera Nayarit atmosphere. Onyx delivers more infrastructure for families with children of varying ages and a more conventional but genuinely functional Caribbean beach. If you want a refined Pacific Mexico all-inclusive with outstanding rooms and service in a surf-coast setting, choose Bahia Mita. If you want a feature-rich Dominican family resort with waterparks, a lazy river, and a proper beach, choose Dreams Onyx.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and couples who want a high-quality Pacific Mexico all-inclusive near Punta de Mita, where exceptional rooms, cleanliness, and service matter more than a calm swimming beach or a large suite of water attractions. Best suited to those drawn to the Riviera Nayarit's rugged coastal character.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children across a wide age range who want a well-rounded Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, teen club, swim-up bar, and a proper Caribbean beach, all at a strong value rating. Particularly good for larger groups needing rooms for five or more.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Bahia Mita is best visited November through April, when the Pacific coast is dry and the surf is active but manageable. Avoid summer hurricane season on the Pacific. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana is most reliably sunny December through April; the Dominican Republic's hurricane season peaks August through October, though Punta Cana's eastern position gives it somewhat lower storm risk than other Caribbean destinations.","activities":"At Dreams Bahia Mita, guests can surf or watch world-class breaks, take boat trips to the Marietas Islands, snorkel, kayak, or visit nearby Sayulita and the town of Punta de Mita. At Dreams Onyx, guests can use on-site waterparks, the lazy river, swim-up bar, and adult pool, or venture off-resort to Punta Cana's zip-line parks, dune buggy tours, cenote excursions, and the Cap Cana marina."},"dreams-los-cabos-suites-golf-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Los Cabos Suites Golf Resort & Spa is a high-end family all-inclusive on Mexico's Baja Peninsula near San Jose del Cabo, with strong room (8.7), service (8.7), and cleanliness (8.9) scores but a notably weak beach rating (3.3) and a leaner amenity set that lacks a swim-up bar, lazy river, waterpark, and teen club. Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a larger family all-inclusive in the Dominican Republic's Punta Cana with a superior overall score (9.1 vs 8.6), a much better beach (6.5 vs 3.3), higher cleanliness (9.1 vs 8.9), better service (9.0 vs 8.7), and a substantially broader amenity lineup including a lazy river, waterpark for all ages, teen club, adult pool, swim-up bar, and babysitting. Los Cabos wins on dramatic desert-meets-ocean scenery and golf proximity, but Onyx is the more complete family resort with better beach access and a more extensive activity infrastructure at a slightly better value score (8.7 vs 8.3).","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples or families who want the rugged, distinctive landscape of Los Cabos, prioritize immaculate rooms and attentive service, and are happy to venture off-property for beach time. Golfers and those drawn to Baja's dramatic scenery over a conventional Caribbean beach setup will find it a strong fit.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of all ages who want a well-rounded Caribbean all-inclusive with a genuine beach, lazy river, waterparks for big and little kids, a teen club, and babysitting. Those who place a premium on cleanliness, service consistency, and having everything on-site will be well served here.","whenToVisit":"Los Cabos is best from November through May, avoiding summer hurricane season and intense heat; October can bring tropical storms. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana is warm year-round but peak season runs December through April for calm seas and low humidity. Both properties carry premium pricing over Christmas and New Year, so late January through March offers good weather with slightly softer rates.","activities":"Los Cabos guests can golf at nearby courses, take whale-watching tours (December to April), explore the famous El Arco rock formation by boat, go sport fishing, or ATV through the desert. Punta Cana guests at Dreams Onyx have on-site waterparks, a lazy river, and snorkelling, plus easy access to Hoyo Azul cenote, dune buggy excursions, catamaran day trips, and zip-lining through the surrounding jungle."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-st-lucia-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark, lazy river, kids club for under-4s, teen club, adult pool, swim-up bar, babysitting, and evening entertainment, rated overall 9.1 versus Secrets St. Lucia's 8.6. Dreams Onyx scores higher on overall satisfaction, rooms (8.7 vs 8.6), and value (8.7 vs 8.6), while Secrets St. Lucia edges it on food (8.0 vs 7.6), atmosphere (7.8 vs 7.4), service (9.2 vs 9.0), and sleep quality (9.2 vs 9.1). Beach ratings are close and modest at both properties (6.5 vs 6.8). The most fundamental difference is guest profile: Dreams Onyx is built for families with an extensive children's infrastructure, while Secrets St. Lucia is adults-only with a more intimate, romantic atmosphere in a dramatically scenic Saint Lucian setting. Dreams Onyx offers far more amenities on paper; Secrets St. Lucia's narrower amenity list is offset by a quieter, more refined environment with superior food and service scores.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a large Punta Cana all-inclusive packed with kids infrastructure — waterparks, a lazy river, a toddler club, teen club, babysitting, and evening entertainment — at strong value for a $$$$ price point with an outstanding overall rating of 9.1.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or friends seeking a quieter, more refined adults-only escape in scenic Saint Lucia, where superior food scores (8.0), attentive service (9.2), and peaceful sleep quality (9.2) matter more than an extensive amenity list or family-oriented programming.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations are warm year-round. Punta Cana's dry season runs December through April, making it ideal for avoiding hurricane-season risk, though Dreams Onyx stays busy with families during school holidays. Saint Lucia's dry season also peaks December through April, with lush green scenery year-round. Both carry some hurricane risk June through November, though Saint Lucia sits farther south and is historically less affected.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, guests can enjoy on-site waterparks, a lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, gym, and evening entertainment, with Punta Cana's broader resort strip offering golf, dune-buggy excursions, and cenote tours nearby. At Secrets St. Lucia, Saint Lucia's dramatic volcanic landscape enables rainforest hikes, Piton climbs, whale-watching, sailing excursions, and visits to the drive-in volcano at Sulphur Springs."},"dreams-natura-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Both are Dreams-branded family all-inclusives at the same price tier, but they differ meaningfully in amenity depth, beach quality, and overall ratings. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana scores higher across nearly every category: overall 9.1 vs. 8.5, beach 6.5 vs. 4.5, atmosphere 7.4 vs. 6.9, service 9.0 vs. 8.7, and sleep quality 9.1 vs. 8.6. Onyx also carries a substantially larger amenity set — teen club, lazy river, waterpark for both young and older kids, swim-up bar, adult pool, babysitting, gym, spa, and evening entertainment — versus Natura's notably lean offering of beach, a kids club for under-4s, and open-seating restaurants. Natura does edge Onyx on room ratings (8.8 vs. 8.7) and sits in Puerto Morelos, a quieter Mexican coastal town closer to the Riviera Maya's natural attractions. If you want more amenities, a better beach, and higher across-the-board ratings, Onyx is the clear choice. If you want a quieter Mexican setting with well-appointed rooms and a more understated atmosphere, Natura has appeal.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families or couples who prioritize a peaceful, nature-adjacent Mexican resort experience in quieter Puerto Morelos, and who value beautifully appointed rooms and attentive service over a packed amenity roster. Best suited to guests who won't miss a waterpark, swim-up bar, or evening entertainment program.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of all ages who want a comprehensively equipped Dominican Republic all-inclusive — waterparks for big and small kids, a teen club, lazy river, swim-up bar, babysitting, and evening entertainment — backed by a notably strong beach, high service scores, and rooms that accommodate five or more guests.","whenToVisit":"Puerto Morelos (Natura) is best visited November through April, avoiding summer hurricane season and peak humidity. Punta Cana (Onyx) shares a similar optimal window of December through April, when rainfall is lowest and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Both destinations can see tropical storms June through October, with September being the highest-risk month for either location.","activities":"Near Dreams Natura, guests can explore the Puerto Morelos coral reef — one of the best-preserved along the Riviera Maya — plus cenotes, Mayan ruins at Cobá and Tulum, and jungle zip-lining. Near Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana, activities include catamaran excursions, dune-buggy tours, deep-sea fishing, and day trips to Saona Island. On-property, Onyx's waterparks, lazy river, and evening entertainment outpace Natura's quieter, nature-forward setting."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-tulum-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa and Dreams Tulum Resort & Spa are both family-focused, premium-priced all-inclusives, but they differ significantly across nearly every rated category. Onyx, in Punta Cana, outscores Tulum in overall rating (9.1 vs 8.2), food (7.6 vs 7.0), pool (7.4 vs 6.7), atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.8), room (8.7 vs 8.1), value (8.7 vs 7.9), cleanliness (9.1 vs 8.6), and service (9.0 vs 8.5). The amenity gap is even wider: Onyx offers a waterpark for both little and big kids, a lazy river, teen club, adult pool, swim-up bar, babysitting, gym, spa, and evening entertainment, while Tulum's amenity list is strikingly thin, limited to a beach, a kids club for under 4, and no-reservation dining. Beach scores are similarly close and modest at both (6.5 vs 6.3). At the same price tier, Onyx delivers measurably more across facilities, ratings, and family programming, making Tulum hard to justify unless its specific Mexican jungle-coastal setting is the primary draw.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a well-rounded, high-performing Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks for all ages, a lazy river, teen club, babysitting, spa, and evening entertainment, and who prioritize strong service and cleanliness scores at a price point that delivers clear value.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families drawn specifically to the Tulum area of Mexico who value that destination's unique jungle-meets-Caribbean atmosphere above resort amenities, and who travel with very young children needing a kids club but do not require waterparks, a teen program, or an extensive on-property activity lineup.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in the same seasonal window. Peak season runs December through April when rainfall is lowest and crowds are highest. Punta Cana and Tulum share a similar hurricane-season risk from June through November, with September being the most active month. Shoulder months of May and late November offer a balance of lower prices and reasonable weather at both properties.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana, guests can explore the resort's own waterparks, lazy river, and swim-up bar, with nearby excursions to Saona Island, Hoyo Azul cenote, and Bavaro Adventure Park. At Dreams Tulum, the surrounding area is the main draw, with the Tulum archaeological ruins, Gran Cenote, Sian Ka'an Biosphere Reserve, and numerous cenote-diving and snorkelling tours all accessible within a short drive."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-sunscape-coco-punta-cana":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa and Sunscape Coco Punta Cana are both family all-inclusives in Punta Cana, but they sit in meaningfully different tiers. Dreams Onyx carries a $$$$ price tag against Sunscape's $$$, and that gap shows up across nearly every rating: overall (9.1 vs 8.2), food (7.6 vs 6.2), pool (7.4 vs 6.2), atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.2), room (8.7 vs 7.9), and cleanliness (9.1 vs 8.3). Beach scores are actually closer, with Sunscape edging ahead slightly (6.8 vs 6.5). Where Dreams Onyx really pulls away is amenities: a lazy river, waterparks for both small and big kids, an adult pool, a swim-up bar, a spa, a gym, babysitting, evening entertainment, and rooms accommodating five or more guests. Sunscape offers a kids club and teen club and little else beyond the beach. If you want a fuller-featured Dominican family resort with waterparks, a spa, and strong service ratings at a premium price, Dreams Onyx is the clear choice. If budget is the priority and your family's needs are simple, Sunscape Coco is functional at a lower cost.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a premium Punta Cana all-inclusive with waterparks for all ages, a lazy river, a spa, evening entertainment, babysitting, and rooms that fit larger groups — and are willing to pay for the higher level of amenities, service, and overall polish that Dreams Onyx consistently delivers.","whoShouldChooseB":"Budget-conscious families whose main priority is beach time and a kids club in Punta Cana, and who don't need waterparks, a spa, or a wide amenity set. Sunscape Coco offers a serviceable base at a more accessible price point for families keeping a closer eye on costs.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in Punta Cana, so timing advice applies equally. The peak dry season runs December through April, with the lowest humidity, least rainfall, and the busiest — and most expensive — crowds. May and November offer a quieter middle ground with lower rates and manageable weather. The core hurricane season of August through October brings the highest rain risk and the deepest discounts.","activities":"Both resorts front Punta Cana's Caribbean coastline, with calm waters suitable for swimming and watersports. Nearby, guests can arrange excursions to Saona Island, catamaran day trips, ATV tours through the countryside, zip-lining, and golf at several championship courses. Dreams Onyx adds on-site waterparks and a lazy river so families with younger children can fill days without leaving the property, while Sunscape guests will rely more on those off-site excursion operators."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-curacao-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark, kids club, teen club, lazy river, adult pool, swim-up bar, evening entertainment, babysitting, and rooms for groups of five or more. Zoëtry Curaçao Resort & Spa is a small adults-only boutique all-inclusive near Willemstad with superior room quality (8.8) and food ratings (8.1) but a critically low beach score (3.3) versus Dreams Onyx's already modest 6.5. Dreams Onyx scores higher overall (9.1 vs 7.6) and on value (8.7 vs 7.4), while Zoëtry leads on food, atmosphere, and service. The gap is essentially family scale and beach programming versus adults-only intimacy and refined dining in a more culturally interesting destination. If you want a full-featured Dominican family all-inclusive with waterslides, kids programming, and lively evening entertainment, go to Dreams Onyx. If you want a quiet, design-forward adults-only retreat near the historic streets of Willemstad with better food and service but no meaningful beach, go to Zoëtry Curaçao.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of any age who want a large Punta Cana all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and a full evening entertainment program at strong overall value.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples or solo travellers who want a quiet, boutique all-inclusive near Willemstad's UNESCO-listed city centre, prioritising room quality, refined food, and a relaxed atmosphere over a beach experience.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations enjoy warm weather year-round. The Dominican Republic's peak season runs December through April, with hurricane season peaking August to October. Curaçao sits outside the main hurricane belt, making it a reliable year-round destination, though December to April offers the driest and most consistently pleasant conditions at both properties.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can use the on-site waterpark, lazy river, and swim-up bar, with Bavaro-area excursions including dune buggy tours, catamaran trips, and ziplining nearby. Zoëtry Curaçao guests can explore the colourful colonial architecture of Willemstad on foot, snorkel the island's clear-water reefs, and visit Shete Boka National Park or the flamingo sanctuary at Goto Lake."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-puerto-morelos-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa in Punta Cana and Dreams Puerto Morelos Resort & Spa in Mexico's Riviera Maya are both family-focused $$$$-tier all-inclusives, but their ratings tell a clear story. Onyx outperforms Puerto Morelos across virtually every category: overall 9.1 vs 7.8, food 7.6 vs 7.0, pool 7.4 vs 6.7, atmosphere 7.4 vs 6.9, and service 9.0 vs 8.5. Beach scores are low at both, though Onyx edges ahead at 6.5 vs 5.0. Onyx also carries a dramatically broader amenity set — lazy river, teen club, adult pool, swim-up bar, babysitting, spa, gym, evening entertainment, and rooms for 5+ guests — while Puerto Morelos offers little beyond a kids club and waterpark. Both have no-reservation restaurants. Puerto Morelos has marginally better sleep quality (8.3 vs 9.1 at Onyx, actually Onyx leads there too). For families wanting a fuller amenity package and consistently higher-rated experience, Onyx is the stronger choice; Puerto Morelos suits those specifically committed to the Mexican Riviera Maya location.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families of all sizes, including large groups needing rooms for 5 or more, who want a high-rated Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a lazy river, waterparks, teen club, babysitting, spa, and evening entertainment in a well-rounded, consistently well-reviewed package.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families set on a Riviera Maya location near Puerto Morelos who prioritize comfortable rooms and solid service over a broad amenity lineup, and who are willing to accept lower scores on food, beach, and atmosphere in exchange for a Mexican Caribbean setting.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana is best from December through April when the Dominican Republic's dry season delivers reliable sunshine and lower humidity. Dreams Puerto Morelos is also at its best December through April, avoiding the June–October hurricane season and the muggy summer months. Both resorts sit in the Caribbean hurricane belt, so late summer and fall carry weather risk at either property.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, guests can use the onsite waterparks, lazy river, spa, and gym, or venture into Punta Cana for golf, zip-lining, and dune buggy excursions. At Dreams Puerto Morelos, the nearby Mesoamerican Barrier Reef — the world's second largest — makes snorkelling and diving the standout nearby activity, with Cenote tours, Tulum ruins, and Puerto Morelos town all within easy reach."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-sunscape-puerto-vallarta-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a premium Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Punta Cana rated 9.1 overall, with standout scores for cleanliness (9.1), sleep quality (9.1), service (9.0), and rooms (8.7), alongside a full waterpark for both younger and older kids, lazy river, teen club, adult pool, and babysitting. Sunscape Puerto Vallarta is a more budget-friendly Mexican family all-inclusive rated 8.0 overall, with noticeably lower scores across food (6.2 vs 7.6), beach (5.3 vs 6.5), pool (6.0 vs 7.4), and atmosphere (6.2 vs 7.4). Dreams Onyx sits a price tier above Sunscape but justifies it with meaningfully better ratings across nearly every category. Dreams Onyx also carries a broader amenity set including a kids club for under-4s, waterparks, teen club, and rooms accommodating 5 or more guests. Sunscape offers a lower entry price in a Pacific Mexico setting near Puerto Vallarta but trails on almost every measurable quality metric. If you want a high-rated Dominican family all-inclusive with waterparks, excellent service, and larger rooms, go to Dreams Onyx. If budget is the primary driver and a Puerto Vallarta location appeals, Sunscape is the more accessible option.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a premium Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and top-tier service and cleanliness ratings, and who are willing to pay more for a measurably better experience across nearly every category.","whoShouldChooseB":"Budget-conscious families drawn to a Pacific Mexico setting near Puerto Vallarta who prioritize location and value over amenity depth or quality ratings, and for whom the lower price point outweighs the gaps in food, pool, beach, and atmosphere scores.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana is best from December through April when the Dominican Republic's dry season delivers reliable sunshine. Sunscape Puerto Vallarta suits visitors from November through May, Mexico's dry season on the Pacific coast, when humidity drops and rainfall is minimal. Both resorts see peak pricing over Christmas and New Year, so late January through March offers the best balance of good weather and manageable rates at either property.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests have access to a full waterpark for big and little kids, lazy river, adult pool, swim-up bar, spa, gym, and evening entertainment on the Punta Cana resort strip, with nearby excursions to cenotes, Saona Island, and Bavaro's markets. Sunscape Puerto Vallarta sits close to the Malecón boardwalk, old town Puerto Vallarta, and whale-watching excursions from December through March, with snorkelling, zip-lining, and jungle tours available nearby."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-playa-bonita-panama":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark, lazy river, kids and teen clubs, adult pool, swim-up bar, babysitting, spa, gym, and evening entertainment on a Caribbean beach setting. Dreams Playa Bonita Panama is a family all-inclusive near Panama City with a kids club and open-seating restaurants, but very limited amenities beyond that. The rating gaps are stark: Onyx leads overall 9.1 to 7.4, food 7.6 to 6.7, pool 7.4 to 6.6, atmosphere 7.4 to 6.5, and most dramatically on beach 6.5 to 4.0. Room and value scores also favor Onyx at 8.7 versus 7.6 and 7.2. Playa Bonita edges Onyx only on sleep quality and service, both marginally. Onyx offers a vastly broader amenity set at a comparable price point. Playa Bonita's primary differentiator is proximity to Panama City, making it a logical add-on to a city itinerary rather than a destination beach resort in its own right.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a full-featured Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, teen and kids clubs, babysitting, adult pool, and evening entertainment on a Caribbean beach. Onyx consistently earns strong scores across cleanliness, service, rooms, and value, making it a reliable choice for a primary beach holiday.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families pairing a beach stay with Panama City sightseeing who need a convenient all-inclusive base near the capital and can accept a weaker beach and limited on-site amenities. Not a strong standalone beach destination, but workable for travelers whose itinerary centers on Panama rather than pure resort relaxation.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Onyx benefits from the Dominican Republic's dry season, December through April, when Punta Cana sees its lowest rainfall and most reliable sunshine. Dreams Playa Bonita is near Panama City, where the dry season runs mid-December through April as well. Both resorts share broadly similar optimal timing, but Punta Cana's beach conditions give Onyx a clearer advantage outside the dry season window.","activities":"At Dreams Onyx, guests have waterparks, a lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, gym, and evening entertainment on-site, with Punta Cana's excursion market nearby for ziplining, dune buggies, and catamaran trips. At Dreams Playa Bonita, on-site activity options are thin, but Panama City itself offers the Panama Canal, Casco Viejo's UNESCO-listed old quarter, rainforest wildlife tours, and some of Latin America's best urban dining within easy reach."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-sunscape-sabor-cozumel":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a premium Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark for big and little kids, lazy river, teen club, adult pool, swim-up bar, spa, multiple restaurants, babysitting, and evening entertainment. Sunscape Sabor Cozumel is a budget-friendly Mexican family all-inclusive on the island of Cozumel with a beach and very little else listed in its amenity set. The rating gap between these two is substantial across nearly every category: Dreams Onyx leads on overall score (9.1 vs 7.6), food (7.6 vs 6.1), beach (6.5 vs 5.8), pool (7.4 vs 5.8), atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.2), room (8.7 vs 7.2), and cleanliness (9.1 vs 8.0). Sunscape Sabor Cozumel's main advantages are its significantly lower price point and Cozumel's world-class diving and snorkelling just offshore, which can compensate for a resort experience that is decidedly more basic. If you want a full-featured Dominican family resort with waterparks and strong across-the-board ratings, choose Dreams Onyx. If Cozumel's marine life is the destination and the resort is secondary, Sunscape Sabor offers a low-cost base.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a premium, amenity-rich Dominican all-inclusive with waterparks for all ages, a lazy river, teen club, babysitting, and high marks for food, rooms, and service, and for whom the resort experience itself is central to the holiday.","whoShouldChooseB":"Budget-conscious families or diving and snorkelling enthusiasts who want an affordable base on Cozumel to access the island's extraordinary reef system, and are happy with a simpler resort experience in exchange for significant savings.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations have similar Caribbean seasonality. Peak dry season runs December through April, offering the best beach and pool weather. Cozumel's underwater visibility is exceptional year-round but peaks in the dry season. Both destinations sit inside the Atlantic hurricane belt, so summer and early autumn travel carries weather risk. Shoulder months of May and November offer lower prices with generally acceptable conditions at both properties.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests have on-site waterparks, a lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, and evening entertainment without leaving the resort. Sunscape Sabor Cozumel's greatest asset is off-property: the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef directly offshore offers world-class scuba diving and snorkelling, and the island has cycling routes, Mayan ruins at San Gervasio, and the colourful streets of San Miguel town within easy reach by taxi or rental bike."},"dreams-cozumel-cape-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Cozumel Cape Resort & Spa is a family all-inclusive on the island of Cozumel, Mexico, known for world-class diving and snorkelling access, with a modest amenity set limited to a kids club for under-4s and open-seating restaurants. Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a family all-inclusive in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, with a dramatically broader amenity package including a waterpark for all ages, lazy river, swim-up bar, teen club, adult pool, babysitting, spa, gym, and evening entertainment. The ratings gap is substantial: Onyx leads on overall score 9.1 vs 7.3, food 7.6 vs 6.8, value 8.7 vs 7.5, cleanliness 9.1 vs 8.5, service 9.0 vs 8.3, and rooms 8.7 vs 8.2. Cozumel edges ahead only on location perception tied to its island setting at 8.3 vs 8.6, though both are comparable there. If you want a Cozumel island base with superior diving and snorkelling at a premium price, go to Dreams Cozumel. If you want a high-performing, amenity-rich Dominican family all-inclusive with strong service and cleanliness scores, go to Dreams Onyx.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and couples who prioritise Cozumel's exceptional diving and snorkelling over resort amenities, are comfortable with a smaller, simpler property, and want a genuine island-base experience rather than a self-contained mega-resort.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of all ages who want a high-scoring, amenity-loaded Punta Cana all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, teen club, swim-up bar, babysitting, and consistently strong service and cleanliness ratings at fair value for a premium property.","whenToVisit":"Cozumel is best visited November through April when seas are calm and visibility for diving and snorkelling peaks; hurricane season runs June through October and can affect the island. Punta Cana's peak season runs December through April; shoulder months of May and November offer lower rates with generally manageable weather. Both destinations share the same Caribbean hurricane window, so travel insurance is advisable outside peak season.","activities":"At Dreams Cozumel, the island itself is the activity draw: world-renowned coral reef diving, snorkelling at Palancar and Colombia reefs, deep-sea fishing, and the charming town of San Miguel are all close by. At Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana, on-resort waterparks, a lazy river, and watersports cover most guests' needs, while excursions to Saona Island, dune buggy tours, and zip-lining are readily available nearby."},"dreams-acapulco-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Acapulco Resort & Spa is a family all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast with a modest amenity set — a kids club for under-4s and open-seating restaurants — but little else documented in terms of programmed activities or facilities. Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large, well-appointed family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a beach, kids and teen clubs, lazy river, waterparks for all ages, swim-up bar, adult pool, spa, babysitting, and evening entertainment. The ratings tell the real story: Onyx outscores Acapulco across every single category, with an overall gap of 9.1 versus 7.4, a cleanliness gap of 9.1 versus 7.9, a room gap of 8.7 versus 7.4, a pool gap of 7.4 versus 6.2, and a value gap of 8.7 versus 6.8. Acapulco's only relative strength is its location score of 7.7, though Onyx still leads there at 8.6. Dreams Onyx is simply a more complete, higher-rated resort at a better perceived value; Dreams Acapulco offers Pacific Mexico access but with substantially fewer amenities and weaker guest satisfaction across the board.","whoShouldChooseA":"Guests specifically set on a Pacific Mexico destination or Acapulco itself who can accept a thinner amenity offering and lower guest satisfaction scores in exchange for that location. Best suited to families or couples who prioritize the Mexican Pacific coast over resort facilities.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who want a comprehensively equipped Punta Cana all-inclusive with waterparks for all ages, a teen club, lazy river, swim-up bar, babysitting, and some of the highest cleanliness and service scores in the Dominican Republic — all at a value rating of 8.7.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana is best visited November through April during the Dominican Republic's dry season, avoiding the Atlantic hurricane window of August through October. Dreams Acapulco benefits from Mexico's Pacific dry season of November through April as well, though Acapulco sits outside the main Caribbean hurricane belt. Both resorts see peak pricing and crowds over Christmas, New Year, and spring break.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can enjoy on-site waterparks, a lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, and evening entertainment, with Punta Cana's broader tourism infrastructure — dune buggies, deep-sea fishing, cenote excursions, and Bavaro's shopping — nearby. Dreams Acapulco sits near Acapulco Bay, where cliff diving at La Quebrada, sport fishing, and historic Fort San Diego are accessible, though the resort's own programmed activity offering appears limited by comparison."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-secrets-aura-cozumel":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, loaded with amenities: a waterpark for big and little kids, lazy river, teen club, kids club for under 4, babysitting, adult pool, swim-up bar, evening entertainment, spa, and gym. Secrets Aura Cozumel is a stripped-down adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Cozumel island with a minimal amenity set, its main draw being proximity to world-class diving and snorkelling reefs rather than on-property features. The rating gap is significant: Dreams Onyx scores 9.1 overall versus Secrets Aura's 7.4, with Dreams also leading on food (7.6 vs 7.3), pool (7.4 vs 6.9), rooms (8.7 vs 7.6), value (8.7 vs 7.2), and cleanliness (9.1 vs 8.1). Both beaches rate poorly, but Secrets Aura's 5.5 is notably weaker than Dreams Onyx's 6.5. Secrets Aura edges Dreams Onyx only marginally on service (8.3 vs 9.0, actually Dreams wins) and sleep quality (8.3 vs 9.1, Dreams wins again). By nearly every measurable metric, Dreams Onyx outperforms Secrets Aura at the same price tier.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a feature-rich Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, teen club, babysitting, and evening entertainment in a well-rated, high-cleanliness property where rooms comfortably sleep five or more.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults-only couples or solo travellers drawn specifically to Cozumel's legendary coral reef diving and snorkelling who want a quieter, no-kids base and are willing to accept a more limited on-property experience in exchange for unmatched underwater access just offshore.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations are best visited December through April when Caribbean and Mexican Caribbean weather is driest and most settled. Cozumel's dive visibility peaks in the dry season. Punta Cana's hurricane season runs June through November, with peak risk in September and October. Secrets Aura sits in a similar hurricane belt, so both carry comparable weather risk in the off-season.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can use the on-site waterparks, lazy river, spa, and gym, with Punta Cana's beaches, dune buggy excursions, and Saona Island day trips nearby. Secrets Aura guests have minimal on-property activity but sit steps from some of the world's best scuba diving and snorkelling on the Mesoamerican Reef, plus Cozumel town for dining, shopping, and cenote day trips to the mainland."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-sunscape-curacao-resort-spa-and-casino":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large Punta Cana family all-inclusive with a waterpark for all ages, lazy river, kids and teen clubs, adult pool, swim-up bar, babysitting, evening entertainment, and rooms for groups of five or more. Sunscape Curacao is a family all-inclusive near Willemstad with a spa and casino, but with a notably thinner amenity set. The ratings tell the clearest story: Dreams Onyx outscores Sunscape Curacao across nearly every category, with an overall rating of 9.1 versus 7.3, food at 7.6 versus 6.2, pool at 7.4 versus 6.0, atmosphere at 7.4 versus 6.2, and service at 9.0 versus 7.8. Room quality (8.7 vs 7.4) and value (8.7 vs 7.2) also favor Dreams Onyx significantly. Sunscape Curacao's strongest card is its location score of 8.1, close to Willemstad's colorful UNESCO-listed waterfront, which gives it a cultural edge Dreams Onyx cannot match. For families prioritizing resort amenities and overall quality, Dreams Onyx is the stronger choice by a wide margin.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families who want a high-performing Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, teen and kids clubs, babysitting, and evening entertainment in a well-rated resort where food, service, and room quality consistently deliver across the board.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples drawn to Curaçao's distinctive Dutch-Caribbean culture and proximity to Willemstad's UNESCO waterfront who are willing to accept more modest resort ratings in exchange for a genuinely unique island setting with a casino on site.","whenToVisit":"Punta Cana is best visited December through April during the dry season, avoiding the Atlantic hurricane peak of August through October. Curaçao sits outside the hurricane belt and enjoys reliable sunshine year-round, making Sunscape Curacao a more flexible choice for travel timing, particularly appealing during the summer months when Caribbean hurricane risk is highest.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests can enjoy onsite waterparks, a lazy river, swim-up bar, spa, and evening entertainment, with Punta Cana's excursion market offering zip-lining, dune buggies, and catamaran trips nearby. Sunscape Curacao guests can explore Willemstad's colorful Handelskade waterfront, visit the Hato Caves, dive world-class coral reefs, and tour local distilleries producing authentic Curaçao liqueur."},"dreams-curacao-resort-spa-and-casino-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Curaçao and Dreams Onyx are both $$$$-tier family all-inclusives in the Dreams brand, but their ratings tell starkly different stories. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana scores a 9.1 overall versus Curaçao's 6.4, a gap that runs through nearly every category: service (9.0 vs. 7.3), cleanliness (9.1 vs. 7.8), rooms (8.7 vs. 7.3), value (8.7 vs. 6.4), and sleep quality (9.1 vs. 8.2). Onyx also wins on beach (6.5 vs. 5.3) and pool (7.4 vs. 6.7). Amenity depth is no contest either — Onyx offers a lazy river, waterparks for both ages, teen club, adult pool, swim-up bar, spa, babysitting, and rooms for five or more guests, while Curaçao's list is notably thin. Curaçao's one real advantage is location (7.9 vs. 8.6 favors Onyx, but Curaçao's proximity to Willemstad gives it genuine cultural access unavailable in Punta Cana). For families prioritizing resort quality and amenity breadth, Onyx is the clear choice; Curaçao suits those drawn to a distinctive island destination despite a weaker resort experience.","whoShouldChooseA":"Travelers who want to base themselves near Willemstad's UNESCO-listed Dutch colonial architecture, colorful harbor, and distinct Curaçao culture, and are willing to accept a more limited resort experience and lower overall ratings in exchange for a genuinely different Caribbean destination.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who want a high-performing Punta Cana all-inclusive with strong across-the-board ratings, a lazy river, dual waterparks, teen club, swim-up bar, babysitting, and rooms large enough for five or more — and who prioritize resort quality and value over destination novelty.","whenToVisit":"Curaçao sits outside the hurricane belt, making it reliably dry and sunny year-round, with peak season running December through April. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana follows the standard Dominican Republic pattern: visit December through April for lowest rainfall and lowest humidity. Both properties share similar peak pricing windows, but Curaçao's off-season carries less weather risk than Punta Cana's August–October hurricane exposure.","activities":"Dreams Curaçao guests can explore Willemstad's Handelskade waterfront, snorkel Curaçao's renowned coral reefs, visit Shete Boka National Park, and tour the island's historic Hato Caves. Dreams Onyx guests have access to Punta Cana's long Atlantic beaches, excursions to Saona Island, dune buggy tours, zip-lining, and cenote visits, plus on-property waterparks and a lazy river that keep younger children entertained without leaving the resort."},"breathless-puerto-vallarta-resort-and-spa-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Puerto Vallarta is an adults-only Mexican all-inclusive on the Pacific coast with a strong emphasis on atmosphere and nightlife, posting standout scores for rooms (9.1), cleanliness (9.3), and service (9.2), with a location rating of 8.7 in one of Mexico's most storied resort cities. Dreams Onyx is a family-focused Dominican Republic all-inclusive in Punta Cana loaded with amenities: a waterpark for both age groups, lazy river, kids club for under-4s, teen club, babysitting, adult pool, and rooms that sleep five or more, scoring 8.7 on value versus Breathless's 8.4. Where Breathless edges ahead on room quality (9.1 vs. 8.7) and atmosphere (7.5 vs. 7.4), Dreams Onyx pulls ahead on sleep quality (9.1 vs. 8.5) and pool rating (7.4 vs. 7.0). Beach scores are identical at 6.5, suggesting neither property leads on sand. Breathless suits adults wanting Pacific Mexico's energy and polish; Dreams Onyx suits families who need structured programming and water play infrastructure in the Dominican Republic.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or groups who want a polished, atmosphere-driven all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast with excellent rooms, high service scores, and the cultural draw of Puerto Vallarta nearby, without children in the mix.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of all ages who want a fully equipped Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and large rooms, in a Punta Cana setting that delivers strong value at the same price tier.","whenToVisit":"Breathless Puerto Vallarta is best visited November through April during Mexico's dry season, avoiding summer hurricane risk on the Pacific coast. Dreams Onyx in Punta Cana is also at its driest December through April, though the Dominican Republic's Atlantic-facing coast is less hurricane-prone than the Pacific, making shoulder months like May and November reasonable options for better pricing.","activities":"Breathless guests can explore Puerto Vallarta's Malecón, old town, whale watching (winter), zip-lining in the Sierra Madre, and sport fishing, supplemented by on-site spa and pool programming. Dreams Onyx guests have the waterpark, lazy river, and beach on property, with excursions to Saona Island, Hoyo Azul cenote, Scape Park, and ATV tours through the Punta Cana countryside readily accessible."},"dreams-grand-island-cancun-vs-dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Grand Island Cancun is a family all-inclusive in Costa Mujeres, Mexico, rated highly for service (9.1), cleanliness (9.0), sleep quality (9.0), and location (8.5), but its amenity list is notably thin — the main distinguishing features are a kids club for under-4s and no-reservation dining. Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a family all-inclusive in Punta Cana, Dominican Republic, with a broader amenity set including a waterpark for both young and older kids, lazy river, teen club, adult pool, swim-up bar, babysitting, spa, gym, and rooms for five or more guests. Onyx also edges out Grand Island on food (7.6 vs 7.2), beach (6.5 vs 6.1), pool (7.4 vs 7.1), atmosphere (7.4 vs 6.9), room (8.7 vs 8.3), and value (8.7 vs 7.9). Grand Island holds marginal leads in service and cleanliness but costs more relative to what it delivers. Onyx is the stronger family resort on nearly every measurable dimension; Grand Island suits those prioritizing the Costa Mujeres location specifically.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families or couples who specifically want a quieter, upscale Costa Mujeres setting north of Cancun's main hotel zone, and who prioritize exceptional service scores and sleep quality over a packed amenity list. Best for those who value location and tranquility above waterpark features.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families who want maximum amenities — waterparks for all ages, lazy river, teen club, adult pool, swim-up bar, babysitting, and rooms sleeping five or more — at strong value in Punta Cana. Onyx's higher ratings across food, rooms, atmosphere, and value make it the more practical choice for most family travelers.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when rainfall is lowest and humidity manageable. Costa Mujeres can see Atlantic swells affect beach conditions in winter; Punta Cana's trade winds keep temperatures steady year-round but hurricane season (June–November) brings risk to both. Shoulder months of May and November offer lower prices at either resort with generally acceptable weather.","activities":"At Dreams Grand Island, the quieter Costa Mujeres strip means most activity stays on property; nearby Isla Mujeres is a short ferry ride for snorkeling and golf-cart exploration. At Dreams Onyx, Punta Cana's infrastructure supports day trips to Saona Island, dune-buggy excursions, deep-sea fishing, and cave snorkeling at Hoyo Azul, alongside the resort's own waterparks, lazy river, and evening entertainment program."}}
